xldv20SnmLctTrapFlowControl.description: TMN specific flag to suppress or not autonomous messages to LCT. Default is noTraps after reload or first time power up.

xldv20SnmControlReq.name: xldv20SnmControlReq
xldv20SnmControlReq.description: The user command to start an update of SNMP configuration file .

xldv20SnmControlStatus.name: xldv20SnmControlStatus
xldv20SnmControlStatus.description: The status of control request. The start of an update of the configuration file will only be started if the SnmControlStatus is not requestBusy.

xldv20SnmLctConnected.name: xldv20SnmLctConnected
xldv20SnmLctConnected.description: If a LCT is connected to the DSLAM the attribute will be set .

xldv20SnmTmnConnected.name: xldv20SnmTmnConnected
xldv20SnmTmnConnected.description: The attribute is set by TMN-OS to indicate the receipt of the trap 'startupEnd' .

xldv20SnmMaxResponseTime.name: xldv20SnmMaxResponseTime
xldv20SnmMaxResponseTime.description: TMN-OS maximum wait time in seconds for responses .

xldv20SnmTmnMaxNumber.name: xldv20SnmTmnMaxNumber
xldv20SnmTmnMaxNumber.description: The maximum number of TMNs which can be connected.

xldv20SnmTmnSpecificIndex.name: xldv20SnmTmnSpecificIndex
xldv20SnmTmnSpecificIndex.description: The specific index of a TMN which can be connected.

xldv20SnmCallpPollingFlag.name: xldv20SnmCallpPollingFlag
xldv20SnmCallpPollingFlag.description: The TMN can poll this global alarm flag to see whether for any COH object an alarm is present.

xldv20SnmLctSessionPollingFlag.description: The TMN can poll this flag to see whether an LCT session has been terminated within the last polling period (value set). During the LCT session DSLAM configuration data may have been changed and therefore the TMN database is inconsistent. The TMN can perform a discovery to sychronize the data. The TMN should set the value to notSet before the discovery.

xldv20SnmControlReqResult.name: xldv20SnmControlReqResult
xldv20SnmControlReqResult.description: Result of the last user command.

xldv20SnmControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20SnmControlTimeStamp
xldv20SnmControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20TmnTable.name: xldv20TmnTable
xldv20TmnTable.description: Table for TMN specific data. Instances of this managed entity shall be automatically SNMP configuration file has been read.

xldv20TmnEntry.name: xldv20TmnEntry
xldv20TmnEntry.description: An entry in the xldv20TmnTable. Notifications : none.

xldv20TmnIndex.name: xldv20TmnIndex
xldv20TmnIndex.description: Index of TmnTable. Entries of the table with same index belong to the same TMN.

xldv20TmnOrLctTerminal.name: xldv20TmnOrLctTerminal
xldv20TmnOrLctTerminal.description: Specifies a LCT or TMN terminal.

xldv20TmnInOrOutBand.name: xldv20TmnInOrOutBand
xldv20TmnInOrOutBand.description: Specifies whether communication is in or outband.

xldv20TmnConnected.name: xldv20TmnConnected
xldv20TmnConnected.description: The attribute indicates whether this TMN/LCT is connected.

xldv20TmnTrapFlowControl.description: To suppress or not autonomous messages to TMN-OS. Default : noTraps after reload or first time power up.

xldv20TmnLctSessionPollingFlag.name: xldv20TmnLctSessionPollingFlag
xldv20TmnLctSessionPollingFlag.description: TMN specific LCT session polling flag.

xldv20ActControlReq.name: xldv20ActControlReq
xldv20ActControlReq.description: COH (Connection Handling) user commands. Notifications : xldv20TrStateChangeOper. xldv20TrActCcCreation. xldv20TrActCcDeletion. xldv20TrActCcReload .

xldv20ActControlStatus.name: xldv20ActControlStatus
xldv20ActControlStatus.description: Indicates the status of a control request.

xldv20ActVpiNni.name: xldv20ActVpiNni
xldv20ActVpiNni.description: Identifies the VPI value associated with the Local Exchange.

xldv20ActVpiUni.name: xldv20ActVpiUni
xldv20ActVpiUni.description: The VPI value associated with the Network Termination.

xldv20ActVciNni.name: xldv20ActVciNni
xldv20ActVciNni.description: The VCI value associated with the Local Exchange.

xldv20ActVciUni.name: xldv20ActVciUni
xldv20ActVciUni.description: The VCI value associated with the Network Termination.

xldv20ActIfIndex.name: xldv20ActIfIndex
xldv20ActIfIndex.description: The relevant interface index of the connected PPTP .

xldv20ActPeakCellRateUpstream.name: xldv20ActPeakCellRateUpstream
xldv20ActPeakCellRateUpstream.description: The upstream peak cell rate in bit/sec of the cross connect. ( Bit rate per ATM cell is 53*8 bit/sec ).

xldv20ActPeakCellRateDownstream.name: xldv20ActPeakCellRateDownstream
xldv20ActPeakCellRateDownstream.description: The peak cell rate in downstream direction of the cross connect.

xldv20ActCellDelayVariationToleranceUpst.name: xldv20ActCellDelayVariationToleranceUpstream
xldv20ActCellDelayVariationToleranceUpst.description: The cell delay variation tolerance (in micro seconds) in upstream direction of the cross connect.

xldv20ActCellDelayVariationToleranceDown.name: xldv20ActCellDelayVariationToleranceDownstream
xldv20ActCellDelayVariationToleranceDown.description: The cell delay variation tolerance (in micro seconds) in downstream direction of the cross connect.

xldv20ActTrafficType.name: xldv20ActTrafficType
xldv20ActTrafficType.description: The traffic type of the cross connect. Supported traffic types are : cbr : Constant bit rate. ubr : Unspecified bit rate. nrtVbr : Non real time variable bit rate. rtVbr : Real time variable bit rate.

xldv20ActSustainableCellRateUpstream.name: xldv20ActSustainableCellRateUpstream
xldv20ActSustainableCellRateUpstream.description: The upstream sustainable cell rate in bit/sec for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20ActSustainableCellRateDownstream.name: xldv20ActSustainableCellRateDownstream
xldv20ActSustainableCellRateDownstream.description: The downstream sustainable cell rate in bit/sec for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20ActMaximumBurstSizeUpstream.name: xldv20ActMaximumBurstSizeUpstream
xldv20ActMaximumBurstSizeUpstream.description: The upstream maximum burst size in cells for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20ActMaximumBurstSizeDownstream.name: xldv20ActMaximumBurstSizeDownstream
xldv20ActMaximumBurstSizeDownstream.description: The downstream maximum burst size in cells for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20ActSegmentEndPointNni.name: xldv20ActSegmentEndPointNni
xldv20ActSegmentEndPointNni.description: Specifies whether the NNI VplTp/VclTp/VpcTp is a segment endpoint (yes) or a connecting point (no)

xldv20ActSegmentEndPointUni.name: xldv20ActSegmentEndPointUni
xldv20ActSegmentEndPointUni.description: Specifies whether the UNI VplTp/VclTp/VpcTp is a segment endpoint (yes) or a connecting point (no)

xldv20ActEthMode.name: xldv20ActEthMode
xldv20ActEthMode.description: The operational mode of the ethernet configuration: Available modes: bridging, routing, currentCofiguration (default) . In version V20 the Ethernet configuration is performed already when a NT is created. The option currentConfiguration keeps the current configuration data during cross connect creation.

xldv20ActEthE164Isp.name: xldv20ActEthE164Isp
xldv20ActEthE164Isp.description: The telephon number of the Internet Service Provider.

xldv20ActEthIpAddressNt.name: xldv20ActEthIpAddressNt
xldv20ActEthIpAddressNt.description: The IP Address of the NT.

xldv20ActEthIpAddressSubnetMaskNt.name: xldv20ActEthIpAddressSubnetMaskNt
xldv20ActEthIpAddressSubnetMaskNt.description: The subnet mask of the NT.

xldv20ActEthIpAddressCo.name: xldv20ActEthIpAddressCo
xldv20ActEthIpAddressCo.description: The IP Address of the destination NT (office side).

xldv20ActEthIpAddressSubnetMaskCo.name: xldv20ActEthIpAddressSubnetMaskCo
xldv20ActEthIpAddressSubnetMaskCo.description: The subnet mask of the CO.

xldv20ActEthIpAddressRemoteRouter.name: xldv20ActEthIpAddressRemoteRouter
xldv20ActEthIpAddressRemoteRouter.description: The subnet mask of the ISP router.

xldv20ActTestTypeNni.name: xldv20ActTestTypeNni
xldv20ActTestTypeNni.description: The type of continuity check on NNI side. On F5 level (VC) segment only .

xldv20ActContinuityCheckNni.name: xldv20ActContinuityCheckNni
xldv20ActContinuityCheckNni.description: Specifies whether or not the continuity check at NNI side should be enabled for this instance of the ATM Cross Connection managed entity .

xldv20ActEndpointTypeNni.name: xldv20ActEndpointTypeNni
xldv20ActEndpointTypeNni.description: Specifies whether the NNI termination point VplTp/VclTp/VpcTp during countinuity check should be a source or sink or both (bidirectional connection only).

xldv20ActTestTypeUni.name: xldv20ActTestTypeUni
xldv20ActTestTypeUni.description: The type of continuity check on UNI side. On F5 level (VC) only segment.

xldv20ActContinuityCheckUni.name: xldv20ActContinuityCheckUni
xldv20ActContinuityCheckUni.description: Specifies whether or not the continuity check at UNI should be enabled for this instance of the ATM Cross Connection managed entity.

xldv20ActEndpointTypeUni.name: xldv20ActEndpointTypeUni
xldv20ActEndpointTypeUni.description: Specifies whether the UNI termination point VplTp/VclTp/VpcTp during countinuity check should be source or sink or both (bidirectional connection only).

xldv20ActControlReqResult.name: xldv20ActControlReqResult
xldv20ActControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20ActInbandVpi.name: xldv20ActInbandVpi
xldv20ActInbandVpi.description: The value of the configured inband Vpi. The configured Vpi will be effective only after next reload.

xldv20ActInbandVci.name: xldv20ActInbandVci
xldv20ActInbandVci.description: The value of the configured inband Vci. The configured Vci will be effective only after next reload.

xldv20ActCallpTableIndex.name: xldv20ActCallpTableIndex
xldv20ActCallpTableIndex.description: After a successfull creation or deletion of a cross connect COH provides the index of the created or deleted object.

xldv20ActMaxVciValue.name: xldv20ActMaxVciValue
xldv20ActMaxVciValue.description: Configures the amount of VC's and their VCI values which are created within a VpcTp. Minimum VCI value is 32. Maximum VCI value is 3500 (due to HW limits).

xldv20ActVbrCDVTUpstream.name: xldv20ActVbrCDVTUpstream
xldv20ActVbrCDVTUpstream.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds) for VBR traffic in upstream direction.

xldv20ActVbrCDVTDownstream.name: xldv20ActVbrCDVTDownstream
xldv20ActVbrCDVTDownstream.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds) for VBR traffic in downstream direction.

xldv20ActControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20ActControlTimeStamp
xldv20ActControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20ActSegmentEndPointNt.name: xldv20ActSegmentEndPointNt
xldv20ActSegmentEndPointNt.description: Specifies whether the VplTp/VpcTp at the NT is a segment endpoint (yes) or a connecting point (no).

xldv20ActTestTypeNt.name: xldv20ActTestTypeNt
xldv20ActTestTypeNt.description: The type of continuity check at NT (segment or endToEnd) .

xldv20ActContinuityCheckNt.name: xldv20ActContinuityCheckNt
xldv20ActContinuityCheckNt.description: Specifies whether or not the continuity check at NT should be enabled . NOTE : continuity check not supported at VccTp (F5 level) .

xldv20ActEndpointTypeNt.name: xldv20ActEndpointTypeNt
xldv20ActEndpointTypeNt.description: Specifies whether the endpoint VplTp/VpcTp at NT should be a source or sink or both (bidirectional connection only) for continuity check cells.

xldv20ActCDVTAutoConfig.name: xldv20ActCDVTAutoConfig
xldv20ActCDVTAutoConfig.description: If yes is selected the policing parameter CDVT (cell delay variation tolerance) is determined automatically depending on the configured cell rate.

xldv20AtmCrossConnectTable.name: xldv20AtmCrossConnectTable
xldv20AtmCrossConnectTable.description: The ATM VP cross connect table. This managed entity is used to represent the cross-connect relationship between two Vpl termination points. Instances of this managed entity shall be automatically created and deleted during ATM Connect and ATM Disconnect actions.

xldv20AtmCrossConnectEntry.name: xldv20AtmCrossConnectEntry
xldv20AtmCrossConnectEntry.description: An entry in the ATM cross connect table.

xldv20AccOperationalState.name: xldv20AccOperationalState
xldv20AccOperationalState.description: Identifies whether or not this instance of the ATM Cross Connection managed entity is capable of performing its normal function ( i.e. switching cells ). Altering this attribute is without reporting this state change via the trap 'xldv20TrStateChangeOper'.

xldv20AccTerminationPointA.name: xldv20AccTerminationPointA
xldv20AccTerminationPointA.description: The instance of the VPL termination point within the DSLAM at the LE side.

xldv20AccTerminationPointZ.name: xldv20AccTerminationPointZ
xldv20AccTerminationPointZ.description: The instance of the VPL termination point within the DSLAM at the NT side.

xldv20AccLineIndex.name: xldv20AccLineIndex
xldv20AccLineIndex.description: The external line index. The TLM interfaces (see IFTable) with same line index blong to the same line.

xldv20AccEthVpcIndex.name: xldv20AccEthVpcIndex
xldv20AccEthVpcIndex.description: For cross connects at the LIETH a pointer to the belonging VpcTp. The value is the entry number in the xldv20VpcTpTable. For all other cross connects the value is always 0.

xldv20AccEthVccIndex.name: xldv20AccEthVccIndex
xldv20AccEthVccIndex.description: For cross connects at the LIETH a pointer to the belonging VccTp. The value is the entry number in the xldv20VccTpTable. For all other cross connects the value is always 0.

xldv20AccAlarmState.name: xldv20AccAlarmState
xldv20AccAlarmState.description: Indicates whether for the cross connect an alarm is present or not.

xldv20AccAdminState.name: xldv20AccAdminState
xldv20AccAdminState.description: This attribute is used to activate (unlock) and deactivate (lock) the VPL cross connection. The cross connect is removed within the ATM ASIC, the configuration data of the cross connect are still available within the DSLAM .

xldv20AccAtmfVplIndex.name: xldv20AccAtmfVplIndex
xldv20AccAtmfVplIndex.description: For cross connects at the ATMF port of NT this value identifies the belonging VplTp . The value is the entry number in the xldv20VplTpTable. For all other cross connects the value is always 0.

xldv20VplTpTable.name: xldv20VplTpTable
xldv20VplTpTable.description: This table contains the entries for Vpl termination points (VplTp).

xldv20VplTpEntry.name: xldv20VplTpEntry
xldv20VplTpEntry.description: Represent the VPL termination points on an ATM NE.

xldv20VplOperationalState.name: xldv20VplOperationalState
xldv20VplOperationalState.description: This read-only attribute identifies whether or not the VPL termination is capable of performing its normal functions (in-service or out-of-service).

xldv20VplVpiValue.name: xldv20VplVpiValue
xldv20VplVpiValue.description: The VPI value associated with the VP link being terminated.

xldv20VplHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20VplHwUnitIndex
xldv20VplHwUnitIndex.description: The HwUnitIndex of HWM sublayer: LU for VplNNi or SU for VplUNI.

xldv20VplIfIndex.name: xldv20VplIfIndex
xldv20VplIfIndex.description: The TLM interface index of the connected PPTP.

xldv20VplPeakCellRateUpstream.name: xldv20VplPeakCellRateUpstream
xldv20VplPeakCellRateUpstream.description: The upstream peak cell rate in bit/sec.

xldv20VplPeakCellRateDownstream.name: xldv20VplPeakCellRateDownstream
xldv20VplPeakCellRateDownstream.description: The downstream peak cell rate in bit/sec.

xldv20VplCellDelayVariationToleranceUpst.name: xldv20VplCellDelayVariationToleranceUpstream
xldv20VplCellDelayVariationToleranceUpst.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds).

xldv20VplCellDelayVariationToleranceDown.name: xldv20VplCellDelayVariationToleranceDownstream
xldv20VplCellDelayVariationToleranceDown.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds).

xldv20VplConnectivityPointer.name: xldv20VplConnectivityPointer
xldv20VplConnectivityPointer.description: This attribute serves as a pointer to the instance of the VPL termination point managed entity instance (in the ATM NE) it is cross connected to.

xldv20VplLineIndex.name: xldv20VplLineIndex
xldv20VplLineIndex.description: This value identifies the belonging line.

xldv20VplSegmentEndPoint.name: xldv20VplSegmentEndPoint
xldv20VplSegmentEndPoint.description: This value specifies whether the VplTp is a segment endpoint (yes) or a connecting point (no).

xldv20VplSustainableCellRateUpstream.name: xldv20VplSustainableCellRateUpstream
xldv20VplSustainableCellRateUpstream.description: The sustainable upstream cell rate in bits/sec for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VplSustainableCellRateDownstream.name: xldv20VplSustainableCellRateDownstream
xldv20VplSustainableCellRateDownstream.description: The sustainable downstream cell rate in bits/sec for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VplMaximumBurstSizeUpstream.name: xldv20VplMaximumBurstSizeUpstream
xldv20VplMaximumBurstSizeUpstream.description: The maximum upstream burst size tolerance in cells for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VplMaximumBurstSizeDownstream.name: xldv20VplMaximumBurstSizeDownstream
xldv20VplMaximumBurstSizeDownstream.description: The maximum downstream burst size tolerance in cells for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VplAlarmSeverityIndex.name: xldv20VplAlarmSeverityIndex
xldv20VplAlarmSeverityIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm severity assignment profile managed entity that contains the severity assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity.

xldv20VplAlarmFilteringIndex.name: xldv20VplAlarmFilteringIndex
xldv20VplAlarmFilteringIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm filtering assignment profile managed entity that contains the filtering assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity. (Not implemented)

xldv20VplCvpIndexSegment.name: xldv20VplCvpIndexSegment
xldv20VplCvpIndexSegment.description: The index of of the related entry in the ContinuityCheckVpTable. The entry is created when the COC is enabled (via command or during cross connect creation).

xldv20VplLOCAlarm.name: xldv20VplLOCAlarm
xldv20VplLOCAlarm.description: Indicates an LOC alarm and its direction.

xldv20VplVbrCDVTUpstream.name: xldv20VplVbrCDVTUpstream
xldv20VplVbrCDVTUpstream.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds) for VBR traffic in upstream direction of the VP cross connect.

xldv20VplVbrCDVTDownstream.name: xldv20VplVbrCDVTDownstream
xldv20VplVbrCDVTDownstream.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds) for VBR traffic in downstream direction of the VP cross connect.

xldv20VpcTpTable.name: xldv20VpcTpTable
xldv20VpcTpTable.description: This table contains the entries for VPC termination points.

xldv20VpcTpEntry.name: xldv20VpcTpEntry
xldv20VpcTpEntry.description: Each entry represents the point in the switch where the VPC and its associated overhead (F4 OAM cells) are terminated or originated. Instances of this managed entity may be created automatically by the ATM NE when VP or VC cross connects are created at at an Ethernet port. Or they are created by command. Similarly instances of this managed entity may be deleted automatically by the ATM NE or as a result of an ATM Cross Connect release request. Notifications : xldv20TrRDI. xldv20TrAIS alarms when fault is detected or cleared. xldv20TrStateChangeOper.

xldv20VpcOperationalState.name: xldv20VpcOperationalState
xldv20VpcOperationalState.description: The operational state identifies whether or not the VpcTp is capable of performing its normal functions.

xldv20VpcVpiValue.name: xldv20VpcVpiValue
xldv20VpcVpiValue.description: Identifies the VPI value associated with the VP link being terminated.

xldv20VpcHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20VpcHwUnitIndex
xldv20VpcHwUnitIndex.description: The unique identifier for hardware units, here the HWM sublayer (LU* or or SU or LI*).

xldv20VpcIfIndex.name: xldv20VpcIfIndex
xldv20VpcIfIndex.description: The interface index of the connected PPTP. For Vpc at LU the PPTP in the LU. For Vpc at SU and LI the PPTP at the LI.

xldv20VpcPeakCellRateUpstream.name: xldv20VpcPeakCellRateUpstream
xldv20VpcPeakCellRateUpstream.description: The upstream peak cell rate in bit/sec of the VP cross connect.

xldv20VpcPeakCellRateDownstream.name: xldv20VpcPeakCellRateDownstream
xldv20VpcPeakCellRateDownstream.description: The downstream peak cell rate in bit/sec of the VP cross connect.

xldv20VpcCellDelayVariationToleranceUpst.name: xldv20VpcCellDelayVariationToleranceUpstream
xldv20VpcCellDelayVariationToleranceUpst.description: The upstream cell delay variation (in micro seconds) of the VpcTp .

xldv20VpcCellDelayVariationToleranceDown.name: xldv20VpcCellDelayVariationToleranceDownstream
xldv20VpcCellDelayVariationToleranceDown.description: The downstream cell delay variation (in micro seconds) of the VpcTp.

xldv20VpcSegmentEndPoint.name: xldv20VpcSegmentEndPoint
xldv20VpcSegmentEndPoint.description: This value specifies whether the VpcTp is a segment endpoint (yes) or a connecting point (no).

xldv20VpcSustainableCellRateUpstream.name: xldv20VpcSustainableCellRateUpstream
xldv20VpcSustainableCellRateUpstream.description: The sustainable upstream cell rate in bits/sec for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VpcSustainableCellRateDownstream.name: xldv20VpcSustainableCellRateDownstream
xldv20VpcSustainableCellRateDownstream.description: The sustainable downstream cell rate in cells/sec for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VpcMaximumBurstSizeUpstream.name: xldv20VpcMaximumBurstSizeUpstream
xldv20VpcMaximumBurstSizeUpstream.description: The maximum upstream burst size tolerance in cells for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VpcMaximumBurstSizeDownstream.name: xldv20VpcMaximumBurstSizeDownstream
xldv20VpcMaximumBurstSizeDownstream.description: The maximum downstream burst size tolerance in cells for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VpcAlarmSeverityIndex.name: xldv20VpcAlarmSeverityIndex
xldv20VpcAlarmSeverityIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm severity assignment profile managed entity that contains the severity assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity.

xldv20VpcAlarmFilteringIndex.name: xldv20VpcAlarmFilteringIndex
xldv20VpcAlarmFilteringIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm filtering assignment profile managed entity that contains the filtering assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity. (Not implemented)

xldv20VpcCvpIndexSegment.name: xldv20VpcCvpIndexSegment
xldv20VpcCvpIndexSegment.description: The index of related entry in ContinuityCheckVpcTpTable concerning an enabled continuity check on segment level.

xldv20VpcCvpIndexEndToEnd.name: xldv20VpcCvpIndexEndToEnd
xldv20VpcCvpIndexEndToEnd.description: The index of related entry in ContinuityCheckVpcTpTable concerning a enabled endToEnd continuity check.

xldv20VpcAISAlarm.name: xldv20VpcAISAlarm
xldv20VpcAISAlarm.description: Indicates an AIS alarm and its direction.

xldv20VpcRDIAlarm.name: xldv20VpcRDIAlarm
xldv20VpcRDIAlarm.description: Indicates an RDI alarm and its direction.

xldv20VpcLOCAlarm.name: xldv20VpcLOCAlarm
xldv20VpcLOCAlarm.description: Indicates an LOC alarm and its direction.

xldv20VpcNumberOfVcs.name: xldv20VpcNumberOfVcs
xldv20VpcNumberOfVcs.description: The number of VCs which are created within the VpcTp. The range of VCI values : 32 plus this number - 1.

xldv20VpcVbrCDVTUpstream.name: xldv20VpcVbrCDVTUpstream
xldv20VpcVbrCDVTUpstream.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds) for VBR traffic in upstream direction of the VpcTp.

xldv20VpcVbrCDVTDownstream.name: xldv20VpcVbrCDVTDownstream
xldv20VpcVbrCDVTDownstream.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds) for VBR traffic in downstream direction of the VpcTp.

xldv20VpcEthVpcIndex.name: xldv20VpcEthVpcIndex
xldv20VpcEthVpcIndex.description: Used to address the corresponding entry in the VpcTpTable. Default is 0.

xldv20VpcAtmfVplIndex.name: xldv20VpcAtmfVplIndex
xldv20VpcAtmfVplIndex.description: Used to address the corresponding entry in the VplTpTable. Default is 0.

xldv20VccTpTable.name: xldv20VccTpTable
xldv20VccTpTable.description: VccTp table for VC termination points. Entries are created for Ethernet NTs when cross connects are created. Entries are deleted with the cross connect.

xldv20VccTpEntry.name: xldv20VccTpEntry
xldv20VccTpEntry.description: Each entry represents the point in the switch where the VCC and its associated overhead (F4 OAM cells) are terminated or originated. Instances of this managed entity may be created automatically by the ATM NE or as a result of an Vpl and Vcl cross connect request at an Ethernet port. Similarly instances of this managed entity may be deleted automatically by the ATM NE as a result of an cross connect deletion request. Notifications : xldv20TrStateChangeOper. xldv20TrObjCreate. xldv20TrObjDelete. xldv20TrRDI. xldv20TrAIS. xldv20TrLOC alarms when fault is detected or cleared.

xldv20VccOperationalState.name: xldv20VccOperationalState
xldv20VccOperationalState.description: The operational state identifies whether or not the VPL termination is capable of performing its normal functions (in-service or out-of-service).

xldv20VccVciValue.name: xldv20VccVciValue
xldv20VccVciValue.description: This attribute identifies the VCI value associated with the VC link being terminated.

xldv20VccAlarmSeverityIndex.name: xldv20VccAlarmSeverityIndex
xldv20VccAlarmSeverityIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm severity assignment profile managed entity that contains the severity assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity.

xldv20VccAlarmFilteringIndex.name: xldv20VccAlarmFilteringIndex
xldv20VccAlarmFilteringIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm filtering assignment profile managed entity that contains the filtering assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity. (Not supported yet).

xldv20VccLineIndex.name: xldv20VccLineIndex
xldv20VccLineIndex.description: This value identifies the belonging line .

xldv20VccIndex.name: xldv20VccIndex
xldv20VccIndex.description: A unique value to identify an entry in the VCC TP table.

xldv20VccAISAlarm.name: xldv20VccAISAlarm
xldv20VccAISAlarm.description: Indicates an AIS alarm and its direction.

xldv20VccRDIAlarm.name: xldv20VccRDIAlarm
xldv20VccRDIAlarm.description: Indicates an RDI alarm and its direction.

xldv20VccLOCAlarm.name: xldv20VccLOCAlarm
xldv20VccLOCAlarm.description: Indicates an LOC alarm and its direction.

xldv20VccCvcIndexSegment.name: xldv20VccCvcIndexSegment
xldv20VccCvcIndexSegment.description: The index of the related entry in the xldv20ContinuityCheckVcTable for an enabled continuity check on segment level.

xldv20VccCvcIndexEndToEnd.name: xldv20VccCvcIndexEndToEnd
xldv20VccCvcIndexEndToEnd.description: The index of the related entry in the xldv20ContinuityCheckVcTable for an enabled endToEnd continuity check.

xldv20VcCrossConnectTable.name: xldv20VcCrossConnectTable
xldv20VcCrossConnectTable.description: The VC cross connect table for Virtual Channel point-to-point cross connections. This managed entity is used to represent the VC-cross-connect relationship between two termination points. Instances of this managed entity shall be automatically created and deleted on VCX Connect and VCX Disconnect actions .

xldv20VcCrossConnectEntry.name: xldv20VcCrossConnectEntry
xldv20VcCrossConnectEntry.description: An entry in the VC cross connect table. Notifications : xldv20TrStateChangeOper.

xldv20VcxOperationalState.name: xldv20VcxOperationalState
xldv20VcxOperationalState.description: The Operational State of Vc cross connect.

xldv20VcxTerminationPointA.name: xldv20VcxTerminationPointA
xldv20VcxTerminationPointA.description: Identifies the instance of the VCL termination point that represents the VCL at the LE side.

xldv20VcxTerminationPointZ.name: xldv20VcxTerminationPointZ
xldv20VcxTerminationPointZ.description: Identifies the instance of the VCL termination point that represents the VCL at the NT side.

xldv20VcxEthVpcIndex.name: xldv20VcxEthVpcIndex
xldv20VcxEthVpcIndex.description: Used to address the corresponding entry in the VpcTpTable. Default is 0.

xldv20VcxEthVccIndex.name: xldv20VcxEthVccIndex
xldv20VcxEthVccIndex.description: Used to address the corresponding entry in the VccTP Table. Default is 0.

xldv20VcxVpcNniIndex.name: xldv20VcxVpcNniIndex
xldv20VcxVpcNniIndex.description: Used to address the corresponding entry at NNI in the VpcTpTable. Default is 0.

xldv20VcxVpcUniIndex.name: xldv20VcxVpcUniIndex
xldv20VcxVpcUniIndex.description: Used to address the corresponding entry at UNI in the VpcTP Table. Default is 0.

xldv20VcxAlarmState.name: xldv20VcxAlarmState
xldv20VcxAlarmState.description: This attribute indicates whether for the cross connect an alarm is present or not.

xldv20VcxAdminState.name: xldv20VcxAdminState
xldv20VcxAdminState.description: This attribute is used to activate (unlock) and deactivate (lock) the VCL cross connection. The cross connect is removed within the ATM ASIC, the configuration data of the cross connect are still available within the DSLAM .

xldv20VcxAtmfVplIndex.name: xldv20VcxAtmfVplIndex
xldv20VcxAtmfVplIndex.description: For cross connects at the ATMF port of NT this value identifies the belonging VplTp . The value is the entry number in the xldv20VplTpTable. For all other cross connects the value is always 0.

xldv20VclTpTable.name: xldv20VclTpTable
xldv20VclTpTable.description: This table contains the entries for the VC links.

xldv20VclTpEntry.name: xldv20VclTpEntry
xldv20VclTpEntry.description: The entries represent the termination of VCLs on an ATM NE. An instance of the VC Cross Connection managed entity may be used to relate two instances of the VCL Termination Point managed entity (i.e. for point-to-point cross connection). Instances of this managed entity may be created automatically by the ATM NE or as a result of an VC cross connect request. Similarly instances of this managed entity may be deleted automatically by the ATM NE or as a result of an VC Cross Connect release request. Notifications: xldv20TrStateChangeOper.

xldv20VclVpiValue.name: xldv20VclVpiValue
xldv20VclVpiValue.description: The VPI value associated with the VC link being terminated.

xldv20VclVciValue.name: xldv20VclVciValue
xldv20VclVciValue.description: The VCI value associated with the VC link being terminated.

xldv20VclHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20VclHwUnitIndex
xldv20VclHwUnitIndex.description: The HwUnitIndex of the dependent HW unit. Here the HWM sublayer: the SU for VclUni or the LU for VclNni .

xldv20VclIfIndex.name: xldv20VclIfIndex
xldv20VclIfIndex.description: The interface index of the connected PPTP. It is the PPTP at the LU for VclUni. The PPTP at the LI for VclNni.

xldv20VclPeakCellRateUpstream.name: xldv20VclPeakCellRateUpstream
xldv20VclPeakCellRateUpstream.description: The upstream peak cell rate in bit/sec of the VC cross connect.

xldv20VclPeakCellRateDownstream.name: xldv20VclPeakCellRateDownstream
xldv20VclPeakCellRateDownstream.description: The downstream peak cell rate in bit/sec of the VC cross connect.

xldv20VclCellDelayVariationToleranceUpst.name: xldv20VclCellDelayVariationToleranceUpstream
xldv20VclCellDelayVariationToleranceUpst.description: The upstream cell delay variation (in micro seconds) of the VC cross connect.

xldv20VclCellDelayVariationToleranceDown.name: xldv20VclCellDelayVariationToleranceDownstream
xldv20VclCellDelayVariationToleranceDown.description: The downstream cell delay variation (in micro seconds) of the VC cross connect.

xldv20VclTrafficType.name: xldv20VclTrafficType
xldv20VclTrafficType.description: This attribute identifies the traffic type of the VC cross connect.

xldv20VclConnectivityPointer.name: xldv20VclConnectivityPointer
xldv20VclConnectivityPointer.description: A pointer to the instance of VclTp it is cross connected to.

xldv20VclSegmentEndPoint.name: xldv20VclSegmentEndPoint
xldv20VclSegmentEndPoint.description: Specifies whether the VclTp is a segment endpoint (yes) or a connecting point (no).

xldv20VclSustainableCellRateUpstream.name: xldv20VclSustainableCellRateUpstream
xldv20VclSustainableCellRateUpstream.description: The sustainable upstream cell rate in bits/sec for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VclSustainableCellRateDownstream.name: xldv20VclSustainableCellRateDownstream
xldv20VclSustainableCellRateDownstream.description: The sustainable downstream cell rate in bits/sec for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VclMaximumBurstSizeUpstream.name: xldv20VclMaximumBurstSizeUpstream
xldv20VclMaximumBurstSizeUpstream.description: The maximum upstream burst size tolerance in cells for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VclMaximumBurstSizeDownstream.name: xldv20VclMaximumBurstSizeDownstream
xldv20VclMaximumBurstSizeDownstream.description: The maximum downstream burst size tolerance in cells for nrtVbr traffic.

xldv20VclAlarmSeverityIndex.name: xldv20VclAlarmSeverityIndex
xldv20VclAlarmSeverityIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm severity assignment profile managed entity that contains the severity assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity.

xldv20VclAlarmFilteringIndex.name: xldv20VclAlarmFilteringIndex
xldv20VclAlarmFilteringIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm filtering assignment profile managed entity that contains the filtering assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity. (Not implemented)

xldv20VclCvcIndexSegment.name: xldv20VclCvcIndexSegment
xldv20VclCvcIndexSegment.description: The index of iof the related entry in the xldv20ContinuityCheckVclTpTable. The entry is created when the continuity check is enabled on segment level.

xldv20VclLOCAlarm.name: xldv20VclLOCAlarm
xldv20VclLOCAlarm.description: Indicates an LOC alarm and its direction.

xldv20VclVpcIndex.name: xldv20VclVpcIndex
xldv20VclVpcIndex.description: A pointer to the belonging VpcTP in the VpcTp table.

xldv20VclVbrCDVTUpstream.name: xldv20VclVbrCDVTUpstream
xldv20VclVbrCDVTUpstream.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds) for VBR traffic in upstream direction of the VclTp.

xldv20VclVbrCDVTDownstream.name: xldv20VclVbrCDVTDownstream
xldv20VclVbrCDVTDownstream.description: The cell delay variation (in micro seconds) for VBR traffic in downstream direction of the VclTp.

xldv20EthernetConfigEntry.name: xldv20EthernetConfigEntry
xldv20EthernetConfigEntry.description: The entry of the Ethernet Configuration Table.

xldv20EthMode.name: xldv20EthMode
xldv20EthMode.description: The operational mode of the ethernet configuration: Available modes: bridging, routing.

xldv20EthE164Isp.name: xldv20EthE164Isp
xldv20EthE164Isp.description: The telephon number of the Internet Service Provider, parameter for ipForwarding- mode

xldv20EthIpAddressNt.name: xldv20EthIpAddressNt
xldv20EthIpAddressNt.description: The IP Address of the NT, parameter for ipForwarding - mode.

xldv20EthIpAddressSubnetMaskNt.name: xldv20EthIpAddressSubnetMaskNt
xldv20EthIpAddressSubnetMaskNt.description: The subnet mask of the NT , parameter for ipForwarding- mode.

xldv20EthIpAddressCo.name: xldv20EthIpAddressCo
xldv20EthIpAddressCo.description: The IP Address of the destination NT (office side), parameter for ipForwarding- mode.

xldv20EthIpAddressSubnetMaskCo.name: xldv20EthIpAddressSubnetMaskCo
xldv20EthIpAddressSubnetMaskCo.description: The subnet mask of the CO , parameter for ipForwarding- mode.

xldv20EthIpAddressRemoteRouter.name: xldv20EthIpAddressRemoteRouter
xldv20EthIpAddressRemoteRouter.description: The subnet mask of the ISP router , parameter for ipForwarding- mode.

xldv20ContinuityCheckVpTable.name: xldv20ContinuityCheckVpTable
xldv20ContinuityCheckVpTable.description: The Continuity Check VP table. Holds entries for enabled continuity checks at VP level. Entries are created when Vpl cross connects or VpcTps with enabled continuity check are created or when continuity check is enabled via command. Entries are deleted when the continuity check is disabled (via xldv20ContinuityCheckControl) .

xldv20ContinuityCheckVpEntry.name: xldv20ContinuityCheckVpEntry
xldv20ContinuityCheckVpEntry.description: The entry represents the attributes of an enabled continuity check at a VplTp or VpcTp. Notifications : none.

xldv20CvpEndpointType.name: xldv20CvpEndpointType
xldv20CvpEndpointType.description: The configured endpoint type (source or sink or both) for countinuity check .

xldv20CvpTestType.name: xldv20CvpTestType
xldv20CvpTestType.description: The configured type of continuity check (segment or endToEnd) .

xldv20CvpOperationalState.name: xldv20CvpOperationalState
xldv20CvpOperationalState.description: Identifies whether an enabled continuity check is is working (value enabled) or not.

xldv20CvpVpTpIndex.name: xldv20CvpVpTpIndex
xldv20CvpVpTpIndex.description: Index of the related VplTp or VpcTp .

xldv20CvpObjectType.name: xldv20CvpObjectType
xldv20CvpObjectType.description: Specifies the type of related COH object ( VplTp or VpcTp ) .

xldv20ContinuityCheckVcTable.name: xldv20ContinuityCheckVcTable
xldv20ContinuityCheckVcTable.description: The continuity check configuration table for COC on VC level. Entries in this table are created when Vcl cross connects with enabled continuity check are created or when the continuity check is enabled via command. Entries are deleted when the continuity check is disabled (via xldv20ContinuityCheckControl) .

xldv20ContinuityCheckVcEntry.name: xldv20ContinuityCheckVcEntry
xldv20ContinuityCheckVcEntry.description: The entry represents the attributes of an enabled continuity check . Notifications : none.

xldv20CvcEndpointType.name: xldv20CvcEndpointType
xldv20CvcEndpointType.description: The configured endpoint type ( source or sink or both) for countinuity check .

xldv20CvcTestType.name: xldv20CvcTestType
xldv20CvcTestType.description: The type of continuity check segment or endToEnd .

xldv20CvcOperationalState.name: xldv20CvcOperationalState
xldv20CvcOperationalState.description: This read-only attribute identifies whether or not a continuitycheck is enabled .

xldv20CvcVcTpIndex.name: xldv20CvcVcTpIndex
xldv20CvcVcTpIndex.description: Index of the related VC object (currently VclTp only) .

xldv20CvcObjectType.name: xldv20CvcObjectType
xldv20CvcObjectType.description: Specifies the type of related COH VC object ( VclTp ) .

xldv20CocControlReq.name: xldv20CocControlReq
xldv20CocControlReq.description: Control group for activating/deactivating the continuity check at the source/sink of a VPL or VCL connection. The user command attribute to activate a continuity check (continuityCheckRequest) or to deactivate (noRequest). Notifications : none .

xldv20CocControlStatus.name: xldv20CocControlStatus
xldv20CocControlStatus.description: The status of the control request. The value requestIdle will be set after startup/recovery or after a running test was aborted by the SNMP manager.

xldv20CocEndpointType.name: xldv20CocEndpointType
xldv20CocEndpointType.description: This attribute specifies whether the source or sink of a should be enabled/disabled for countinuity check .

xldv20CocObjectType.name: xldv20CocObjectType
xldv20CocObjectType.description: Selects the type of COH object.

xldv20CocTestType.name: xldv20CocTestType
xldv20CocTestType.description: The type of continuity check (segment or endToEnd) .

xldv20CocIndex.name: xldv20CocIndex
xldv20CocIndex.description: If the continuity check should be enabled it is the index of the selected COH object. If the continuity check should be disabled it is the index xldv20VplCvpIndexSegment or xldv20VpcCvpIndexSegment. xldv20VpcCvpIndexEndToEnd or xldv20VclCvcIndexSegment.

xldv20CocControlReqResult.name: xldv20CocControlReqResult
xldv20CocControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20CocControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20CocControlTimeStamp
xldv20CocControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20InbandVpiCurrent.name: xldv20InbandVpiCurrent
xldv20InbandVpiCurrent.description: Inband TMN configuration object. Identifies the current VPI value of inband TMN channel.

xldv20InbandVciCurrent.name: xldv20InbandVciCurrent
xldv20InbandVciCurrent.description: Identifies the current Vci value of inband TMN channel.

xldv20InbandVpiConfig.name: xldv20InbandVpiConfig
xldv20InbandVpiConfig.description: Identifies the configured Vpi value of inband TMN channel which becomes effective only after reload.

xldv20InbandVciConfig.name: xldv20InbandVciConfig
xldv20InbandVciConfig.description: Identifies the configured Vci value of inband TMN channel which becomes effective only after reload.

xldv20NeLocation.name: xldv20NeLocation
xldv20NeLocation.description: Describes the location of the NetElement, e.g. Hofmannstr. 51 .

xldv20NeVendor.name: xldv20NeVendor
xldv20NeVendor.description: Contains the vendor of the NetElement, Siemens AG .

xldv20NeVersion.name: xldv20NeVersion
xldv20NeVersion.description: Contains the version of the NetElement, XLD V20

xldv20NeExternalTime.name: xldv20NeExternalTime
xldv20NeExternalTime.description: The external Time of the NetElement in seconds from January 1st 1970. The TMN-OS should set this time after firsttime power up, coldstart, warmstart or reload and to refresh it once a day.

xldv20NeTimeZone.name: xldv20NeTimeZone
xldv20NeTimeZone.description: Specifies the time zone of the netelement as time difference to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), e.g. GMT+1 or GMT-5.

xldv20NeDescriptorFileName.name: xldv20NeDescriptorFileName
xldv20NeDescriptorFileName.description: The name of the descriptor file. Initialized after reload by SW upgrade .

xldv20NeExternalTime45020.name: xldv20NeExternalTime45020
xldv20NeExternalTime45020.description: The external Time of the NetElement in seconds. The TMN-45020 sets this time after first time power up, coldstart, warmstart or reload and refreshes the time in a period of 24h . The basis is January 1st 1999, 0:00

xldv20NeSummerTime.name: xldv20NeSummerTime
xldv20NeSummerTime.description: Specifies whether summer time (day light saving time DST) or winter time is valid. Normally the clock is turned 1 hour ahead at begin of summer time and 1 hour back at end. Default is winterTime.

xldv20HwUnitTable.name: xldv20HwUnitTable
xldv20HwUnitTable.description: The XLD hardware unit table. This table models the Equipment, Equipment Holder and Plug-In Unit management entities .

xldv20HwUnitEntry.name: xldv20HwUnitEntry
xldv20HwUnitEntry.description: An entry in the xldv20HwUnitTable. Notifications : none.

xldv20HwUnitIndex.name: xldv20HwUnitIndex
xldv20HwUnitIndex.description: A unique value to identify a hardware unit within the ATM agent. It is used as index for the tables xldv20HwEquipTable, xldv20HwEquipHolderTable and xldv20HwPlugInUnitTable .

xldv20HwUnitType.name: xldv20HwUnitType
xldv20HwUnitType.description: Identifies the general type of this hardware unit. The values are equipment, equipmentHolder and plugInUnit .

xldv20HwContainmentTable.name: xldv20HwContainmentTable
xldv20HwContainmentTable.description: The hardware unit containment table. This table describes the containment relationships that maintain between Equipment, Equipment Holder and Plug-In Unit entities .

xldv20HwContainmentEntry.name: xldv20HwContainmentEntry
xldv20HwContainmentEntry.description: An entry in the hardware unit containment table. Each entry of this type identifies two hardware units, one of which is contained directly within the other . Notifications : none.

xldv20HwContainingUnitIndex.name: xldv20HwContainingUnitIndex
xldv20HwContainingUnitIndex.description: The HwUnitIndex (in the xldv20HwUnitTable), of the containing hardware unit in this pair .

xldv20HwContainedUnitAddr.name: xldv20HwContainedUnitAddr
xldv20HwContainedUnitAddr.description: A number uniquely identifying, within the containing hardware unit, the contained unit. Contained unit should be addressed starting at 1. If the contained component is an Equipment Holder, this object represents its physical location (e.g. slot number). If a single piece of Equipment contains both Equipment Holder and other Equipment objects, the Equipment Holders should have the lowest-valued addresses, so this relationship can be maintained. A Plug-In Unit always has an address of 1 .

xldv20HwContainedUnitIndex.name: xldv20HwContainedUnitIndex
xldv20HwContainedUnitIndex.description: The hwUnitIndex of the contained unit.

xldv20HwEquipEntry.name: xldv20HwEquipEntry
xldv20HwEquipEntry.description: Entry of the HW equipment table. The entries represent the various manageable physical components of the ATM NE that are not modelled via the Plug-In Unit managed entity. An instance of this managed entity shall be automati- cally created by the ATM NE immediately following the initialization/installation of the externally manageable physical component in the ATM NE. Notifications : xldv20TrObjCreate. xldv20TrObjDelete .

xldv20EquType.name: xldv20EquType
xldv20EquType.description: Indicates whether the equipment is a DSLAM, ntAdsl, ntVdsl or a ntCpe ( customer premise equipment) .

xldv20EquLocation.name: xldv20EquLocation
xldv20EquLocation.description: Identifies the specific or general location of the ATM NE component .

xldv20EquUserLabel.name: xldv20EquUserLabel
xldv20EquUserLabel.description: Assignis user friendly name to the associated managed entity .

xldv20EquConnectedPiuIndex.name: xldv20EquConnectedPiuIndex
xldv20EquConnectedPiuIndex.description: This attribute is used to show the PIU to which the NT is connected (HwUnitIndex) . In case of DSLAM value is 0.

xldv20EquConnectedPiuPort.name: xldv20EquConnectedPiuPort
xldv20EquConnectedPiuPort.description: The port ID of the connected PIU.

xldv20HwEquipHolderEntry.name: xldv20HwEquipHolderEntry
xldv20HwEquipHolderEntry.description: Entry of the equipment holder table. The entries represent physical resources of the ATM NE holding other physical resources. Examples of resources represented by instances of this managed entity are shelves and slots. An instance of this managed entity shall exist for each shelf and slot of the ATM NE. Instances shall be auto- matically created and reported by the ATM NE once system initialization is complete. Notifications : xldv20TrObjCreate . xldv20TrObjDelete . xldv20TrSwVersionSet when xldv20EqhSwVersion. xldv20EqhMnemoCode,xldv20EqhFwItemNumber set.

xldv20EqhAccPiuTypes.name: xldv20EqhAccPiuTypes
xldv20EqhAccPiuTypes.description: Accepted PIU Types of this slot. This attribute identifies the types of Plug-In Units to be supported by this slot. They are separated by newline characters. That means 'CR LF'. This attribute only supplies if the Equipment holder instance represents a slot.

xldv20EqhSlotStatus.name: xldv20EqhSlotStatus
xldv20EqhSlotStatus.description: Indicates whether a slot is empty or used. This attribute only supplies if the Equipment holder instance represents a slot.

xldv20EqhSwVersion.name: xldv20EqhSwVersion
xldv20EqhSwVersion.description: Identifies the software load of this PIU. This attribute identifies the software load, if there is any, which is currently designated as the one to be loaded to the plug-in-unit whenever an automatic reload of software is needed. This attribute only applies if the equipment holder instance represents a slot. Default value for not loadable units is \0 .

xldv20EqhMnemoCode.name: xldv20EqhMnemoCode
xldv20EqhMnemoCode.description: The mnemo code used to retrieve the SW loadfile for the plug-in unit. Default value for not loadable units is \0 .

xldv20EqhFwCode.name: xldv20EqhFwCode
xldv20EqhFwCode.description: The FW code used to retrieve the SW loadfile for the plug-in unit. Default value for not loadable units is \0 .

xldv20EqhRiMnemoCode.name: xldv20EqhRiMnemoCode
xldv20EqhRiMnemoCode.description: This attribute specifies the mnemo code of the currently plugged PIU.

xldv20EqhRiFwItemNumber.name: xldv20EqhRiFwItemNumber
xldv20EqhRiFwItemNumber.description: This attribute specifies the FW item number of the currently plugged PIU.

xldv20EqhRiFwIssue.name: xldv20EqhRiFwIssue
xldv20EqhRiFwIssue.description: This attribute specifies the FW item issue of the currently plugged PIU.

xldv20EqhRiHwItemNumber.name: xldv20EqhRiHwItemNumber
xldv20EqhRiHwItemNumber.description: This attribute specifies the HW item number of the currently plugged PIU.

xldv20EqhRiHwIssue.name: xldv20EqhRiHwIssue
xldv20EqhRiHwIssue.description: This attribute specifies the HW item issue of the currently plugged PIU.

xldv20EqhRiSerialNumber.name: xldv20EqhRiSerialNumber
xldv20EqhRiSerialNumber.description: This attribute specifies the Serial Number of the currently plugged PIU.

xldv20HwPlugInUnitTable.name: xldv20HwPlugInUnitTable
xldv20HwPlugInUnitTable.description: Table containing the plug-in unit entries .

xldv20HwPlugInUnitEntry.name: xldv20HwPlugInUnitEntry
xldv20HwPlugInUnitEntry.description: Entry of plug in unit table. Each entry is used to represent equipment that is inserted (plugged into) and removed from slots of the ATM NE . Notifications : xldv20TrStateChangeOper. xldv20TrStateChangeAdmin. xldv20TrTrObjCreate. xldv20TrObjDelete. Alarm traps when a fault has been detected or cleared.

xldv20PiuAdminState.name: xldv20PiuAdminState
xldv20PiuAdminState.description: This attribute is used to activate (unlock) and deactivate (lock) the functions performed by the plug-in unit. Default is locked except for LU155:OM, LU155:OL, LUPON:O, LUDSX3:C. For LU155:OM, LU155:OL, LUPON:O, LUDSX3:C locking is only allowed from LCT. In the transition from lock to unlock the Plug-In Unit is diagnosed.

xldv20PiuAvailStatus.name: xldv20PiuAvailStatus
xldv20PiuAvailStatus.description: The availability status of a plug-in unit is described with this attribute.

xldv20PiuOperState.name: xldv20PiuOperState
xldv20PiuOperState.description: The operational state of plug in unit.

xldv20PiuType.name: xldv20PiuType
xldv20PiuType.description: Identifier for the type of a plug-in unit. See description of xldv20EqhAccPiuTypes for possible string values.

xldv20PiuAlarmSeverityIndex.name: xldv20PiuAlarmSeverityIndex
xldv20PiuAlarmSeverityIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm severity assignment profile managed entity that contains the severity assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity. Default is 1.

xldv20PiuAlarmFilteringIndex.name: xldv20PiuAlarmFilteringIndex
xldv20PiuAlarmFilteringIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm filtering assignment profile managed entity that contains the filtering assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity. (Not implemented yet) .

xldv20PiuUpgradeResult.name: xldv20PiuUpgradeResult
xldv20PiuUpgradeResult.description: Informs about the status of the SW upgrade task during loading and the result at the end of loading the current plug-in unit.

xldv20HwuControlReq.name: xldv20HwuControlReq
xldv20HwuControlReq.description: This attribute identifies the control command for creating or deleting a HW unit. Notifications : xldv20TrHwuControl when command is finished.

xldv20HwuControlStatus.name: xldv20HwuControlStatus
xldv20HwuControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

xldv20HwuUnitType.name: xldv20HwuUnitType
xldv20HwuUnitType.description: Identifies the type of hardware unit which should be created. The values are equipment, equipmentHolder and plugInUnit . The following entities can not be created: atmNe. equipment (DSLAM). equipmentHolder (basic shelf). equipmentHolder (slot1-slot32 of basic shelf).

xldv20HwuEquType.name: xldv20HwuEquType
xldv20HwuEquType.description: Indicates the equipment which should be created (ntAdsl or ntVdsl or ntCpe). Default is \0.

xldv20HwuEqhType.name: xldv20HwuEqhType
xldv20HwuEqhType.description: Indicates the equipmentHolder which should be created (extendedShelf or ntAdslShelf or ntVdslShelf) .

xldv20HwuPiuType.name: xldv20HwuPiuType
xldv20HwuPiuType.description: Identifies the type of a plug-in unit which should be created. The following entities cannot be created or deleted : LU*, and CI . Default is \0.

xldv20HwuContainingUnitIndex.name: xldv20HwuContainingUnitIndex
xldv20HwuContainingUnitIndex.description: Identifies the managed entity which contains the created unit .

xldv20HwuContainedUnitAddr.name: xldv20HwuContainedUnitAddr
xldv20HwuContainedUnitAddr.description: Identifies the index of the contained unit, which should be created, within the containing unit .

xldv20HwuUnitIndex.name: xldv20HwuUnitIndex
xldv20HwuUnitIndex.description: Identifies the HW Unit which should be deleted .

xldv20HwuControlTimer.name: xldv20HwuControlTimer
xldv20HwuControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager when a create or delete HW unit request cannot be executed immediately ( value commExecStarted in GetResponse for xldv20HwuControlReq ).

xldv20HwuControlReqResult.name: xldv20HwuControlReqResult
xldv20HwuControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20HwuControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20HwuControlTimeStamp
xldv20HwuControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20RiControlReq.name: xldv20RiControlReq
xldv20RiControlReq.description: Feature not supported. This attribute identifies the control commands to get information about the boards currently plugged into the XLD system. On a request from TMN-OS or LCT, the Product Identification Data (PID) and location data (rack, row, slot) of either a single board or of all boards plugged are collected. These data are sent to to a file at the FTP server. Notifications : xldv20TrRemInvReady when the remote inventory data have been collected and the resulting file has been sent to the FTP server.

xldv20RiControlStatus.name: xldv20RiControlStatus
xldv20RiControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

xldv20RiControlTimer.name: xldv20RiControlTimer
xldv20RiControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager when remote inventory data retrieve request cannot be executed immediately (value commExecStarted in the result attribute xldv20RiControlReqResult). The manager reads this value from the DSLAM. The end of request indicates the trap xldv20TrRemInvReady .

xldv20RiResultFilePath.name: xldv20RiResultFilePath
xldv20RiResultFilePath.description: The destination path where the file containing the remote inventory data should be stored on the FTP server. If this attribute does not contain a valid path name no remote inventory data will be transmitted .

xldv20RiHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20RiHwUnitIndex
xldv20RiHwUnitIndex.description: The HwUnitIndex of the requested board. if remote inventory data for a single board are requested.

xldv20RiControlReqResult.name: xldv20RiControlReqResult
xldv20RiControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20RiControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20RiControlTimeStamp
xldv20RiControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20HwUnitMappingTable.name: xldv20HwUnitMappingTable
xldv20HwUnitMappingTable.description: The table maps hardware units ('HwUnitIndex') to TLM interfaces ('IfIndex') accociated to this hardware.

xldv20HwmHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20HwmHwUnitIndex
xldv20HwmHwUnitIndex.description: The 'HwUnitIndex' of the selected hardware unit.

xldv20HwmIfIndex.name: xldv20HwmIfIndex
xldv20HwmIfIndex.description: The 'IfIndex' of a TLM interface on the selected hardware unit.

xldv20IfEntry.name: xldv20IfEntry
xldv20IfEntry.description: An entry in the TLM interface table. Each entry represents either a physical path termination point (PPTP) or a TC adaptor (tcAdaptor). Notifications : alarm traps when a fault has been detected or cleared. xldv20TrStateChangeOper. xldv20TrStateChangeAdmin.

xldv20IfIndex.name: xldv20IfIndex
xldv20IfIndex.description: Index of the table. Identifier of a TLM interface .

xldv20IfType.name: xldv20IfType
xldv20IfType.description: The type of a TLM interface. Supported interface types : s1n, s1f. adc, adr. ibm, eth. s3n, s3f. d3n, d3f. e3n, e3f. e1nIma, e1fIma. d1nIma, d1fIma. sdc, sdr. atmIma (IMA group). tca. In XLDV20 unused : pon. vdc. vdr. d1nIma. d1fIma.

xldv20IfLineIndex.name: xldv20IfLineIndex
xldv20IfLineIndex.description: A unique value to identify interfaces belonging to the same line.

xldv20IfHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20IfHwUnitIndex
xldv20IfHwUnitIndex.description: The index to identify the hardware unit the physical path/TC layer terminates on.

xldv20IfHwPortId.name: xldv20IfHwPortId
xldv20IfHwPortId.description: For PPTP it is the associated HW port ID. For TC adaptor it is the IfIndex of the PPTP the TC adaptor is connected to.

xldv20IfConnectivityIndex.name: xldv20IfConnectivityIndex
xldv20IfConnectivityIndex.description: For PPTP it is the associated HW port ID. For TC adaptor it is the IfIndex of the PPTP the TC adaptor is connected to.

xldv20IfOperState.name: xldv20IfOperState
xldv20IfOperState.description: The operational state of this unit.

xldv20IfAdminState.name: xldv20IfAdminState
xldv20IfAdminState.description: Activates(unlock) or deactivates(lock) the functionality of this managed entity. It must be locked before physical looptest has been started. The attribute is not configurable during looptest. The PPTP of type s1f, s3f, e3f, d3f, e1nIma, e1fIma, d1nIma, d1fIma and atmIma and the associated tcAdaptors can only be locked from a connected LCT.

xldv20IfAlarmState.name: xldv20IfAlarmState
xldv20IfAlarmState.description: The nature of an alarm at a TLM interface. Values correspond to alarm trap ID`s. Default is noAlarm.

xldv20IfAlarmSeverityIndex.name: xldv20IfAlarmSeverityIndex
xldv20IfAlarmSeverityIndex.description: The index of the associated entry in the alarm severity profile table. These entries contain the severity assigments for the alarms reported by this managed entity. The range of values is: 1,.., 10: for possible pre-configured alarm severity profiles . Default is profile 1.

xldv20IfAlarmFilteringIndex.name: xldv20IfAlarmFilteringIndex
xldv20IfAlarmFilteringIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm filtering assignment profile managed entity that contains the filtering assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity.

xldv20AdcCtrlControlReq.name: xldv20AdcCtrlControlReq
xldv20AdcCtrlControlReq.description: ADSL control request object to activate a configured set of data (command: activateData), which includes minimum and maximum bandwidth in upstream and downstream direction, latency and margin.

xldv20AdcCtrlControlStatus.name: xldv20AdcCtrlControlStatus
xldv20AdcCtrlControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

xldv20AdcCtrlIfIndex.name: xldv20AdcCtrlIfIndex
xldv20AdcCtrlIfIndex.description: It is the relevant interface index of the ADSL central PPTP.

xldv20AdcCtrlMinRateDn.name: xldv20AdcCtrlMinRateDn
xldv20AdcCtrlMinRateDn.description: Desired lower limit of downstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 to 8096 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 19094 cells/sec. Default is 1 (32 kbps/75 cps).

xldv20AdcCtrlMinRateUp.name: xldv20AdcCtrlMinRateUp
xldv20AdcCtrlMinRateUp.description: Desired lower limit of upstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 to 768 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 1811 cells/sec. Default is 1 (32 kbps/75 cps).

xldv20AdcCtrlMaxRateDn.name: xldv20AdcCtrlMaxRateDn
xldv20AdcCtrlMaxRateDn.description: Desired upper limit of downstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 and 8096 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 19094 cells/sec. Default is 253 (8096 kbps/19094 cps).

xldv20AdcCtrlMaxRateUp.name: xldv20AdcCtrlMaxRateUp
xldv20AdcCtrlMaxRateUp.description: Desired upper limit of upstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 and 768 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 1811 cells/sec. Default is 24 (768 kbps/1811 cps).

xldv20AdcCtrlMarginDn.name: xldv20AdcCtrlMarginDn
xldv20AdcCtrlMarginDn.description: Desired downstream margin in units of dB.

xldv20AdcCtrlMarginUp.name: xldv20AdcCtrlMarginUp
xldv20AdcCtrlMarginUp.description: Desired upstream margin in units of dB .

xldv20AdcCtrlLatencyDn.name: xldv20AdcCtrlLatencyDn
xldv20AdcCtrlLatencyDn.description: Selects fast mode or interleaved mode downstream. 0 = interleavedLow (default). 1 = interleavedHigh . 256 = fast mode.

xldv20AdcCtrlLatencyUp.name: xldv20AdcCtrlLatencyUp
xldv20AdcCtrlLatencyUp.description: Selects fast mode or interleaved mode upstream. 0 = interleavedLow (default). 1 = interleavedHigh . 256 = fast mode.

xldv20AdcCtrlMinMarginDn.name: xldv20AdcCtrlMinMarginDn
xldv20AdcCtrlMinMarginDn.description: Threshold for downstream margin when an alarm should be sent. In units of dB. The value auto is the default value and means that the threshold is calculated from the configured margin : threshold margin down = configured margin down - 6 dB.

xldv20AdcCtrlMinMarginUp.name: xldv20AdcCtrlMinMarginUp
xldv20AdcCtrlMinMarginUp.description: Threshold for upstream margin when an alarm should be sent. In units of dB. The value auto is the default value and means that the threshold is calculated from the configured margin : threshold margin up = configured margin up - 6 dB.

xldv20AdcCtrlControlReqResult.name: xldv20AdcCtrlControlReqResult
xldv20AdcCtrlControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20AdcCtrlXdslServiceType.name: xldv20AdcCtrlXdslServiceType
xldv20AdcCtrlXdslServiceType.description: The service mode for the DSL line according to ITU norm. Supported modes are : - gDotHsMode (handshake mode) for automatic link up either to ADSL equipment . or to UDSL equipment (G9941). - or ansiT1Dot413 for ADSL equipment (fullRateMode, ITU G9921). - or gDotLiteMode for UDSL equipment (uawgMode, ITU G9922). - or gDotAll to allow any NT/CPE service type (is determined by the central modem) .

xldv20AdcCtrlControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20AdcCtrlControlTimeStamp
xldv20AdcCtrlControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20AdcCtrlTrainingMode.name: xldv20AdcCtrlTrainingMode
xldv20AdcCtrlTrainingMode.description: Selects between different training modes for ADSL modems.

xldv20VdcCtrlControlReq.name: xldv20VdcCtrlControlReq
xldv20VdcCtrlControlReq.description: Feature not supported. This attribute marks the command to activate a configured set of (command: activateData), which includes minimum and maximum bandwidth in upstream and downstream direction, latency and some additional modem parameters (power boost, warmstart, VDSL mode, Sleep mode, PSD mask, power adaptation).

xldv20VdcCtrlControlStatus.name: xldv20VdcCtrlControlStatus
xldv20VdcCtrlControlStatus.description: This attribute indicates the status of a control request. requestIdle, requestBusy, requestPassed, requestFailed .

xldv20VdcCtrlIfIndex.name: xldv20VdcCtrlIfIndex
xldv20VdcCtrlIfIndex.description: It is the relevant interface index of the VDSL-C PPTP.

xldv20VdcCtrlMinRateDn.name: xldv20VdcCtrlMinRateDn
xldv20VdcCtrlMinRateDn.description: The desired lower limit of the downstream data rate.

xldv20VdcCtrlMinRateUp.name: xldv20VdcCtrlMinRateUp
xldv20VdcCtrlMinRateUp.description: The desired lower limit of the upstream data rate.

xldv20VdcCtrlMaxRateDn.name: xldv20VdcCtrlMaxRateDn
xldv20VdcCtrlMaxRateDn.description: The upper limit of the downstream data rate.

xldv20VdcCtrlMaxRateUp.name: xldv20VdcCtrlMaxRateUp
xldv20VdcCtrlMaxRateUp.description: The upper limit of the upstream data rate.

xldv20VdcCtrlLatencyDn.name: xldv20VdcCtrlLatencyDn
xldv20VdcCtrlLatencyDn.description: Selects interleave depth (i.e. latency time) used for error correction in downstream direction.

xldv20VdcCtrlLatencyUp.name: xldv20VdcCtrlLatencyUp
xldv20VdcCtrlLatencyUp.description: Selects interleave depth (i.e. latency time) used for error correction in upstream direction.

xldv20VdcCtrlPsdMask.name: xldv20VdcCtrlPsdMask
xldv20VdcCtrlPsdMask.description: Configured PSD mask option (electro-magnetic interference effects, M1 for strong and M2 for weak effects).

xldv20VdcCtrlControlReqResult.name: xldv20VdcCtrlControlReqResult
xldv20VdcCtrlControlReqResult.description: This read-only attribute informs about the result of the last user command.

xldv20VdcCtrlControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20VdcCtrlControlTimeStamp
xldv20VdcCtrlControlTimeStamp.description: This read-only attribute informs about the time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20AdcPPTPTable.name: xldv20AdcPPTPTable
xldv20AdcPPTPTable.description: The physical path termination point table for ADSL Central interface.

xldv20AdcPPTPEntry.name: xldv20AdcPPTPEntry
xldv20AdcPPTPEntry.description: An entry describing a termination point in the PPTP table. Notifications : see xldv20IfEntry.

xldv20AdcMinRateDnCfg.name: xldv20AdcMinRateDnCfg
xldv20AdcMinRateDnCfg.description: The desired lower value of the downstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 to 8096 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 19094 cells/sec. Default is 1 (32 kbps/75 cps).

xldv20AdcMinRateUpCfg.name: xldv20AdcMinRateUpCfg
xldv20AdcMinRateUpCfg.description: The desired lower value of the upstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 and 768 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 1811 cells/sec. Default is 1 (32 kbps/75 cps).

xldv20AdcMaxRateDnCfg.name: xldv20AdcMaxRateDnCfg
xldv20AdcMaxRateDnCfg.description: The desired upper value of the downstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 and 8160 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 1811 cells/sec. Default is 253 (8096 kbps/19094 cps).

xldv20AdcMaxRateUpCfg.name: xldv20AdcMaxRateUpCfg
xldv20AdcMaxRateUpCfg.description: The desired upper value of the upstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 and 768 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 1811 cells/sec. Default is 24 (768 kbps/1811 cps).

xldv20AdcMarginDnCfg.name: xldv20AdcMarginDnCfg
xldv20AdcMarginDnCfg.description: Desired downstream margin. The unit of measurement is dB.

xldv20AdcMarginUpCfg.name: xldv20AdcMarginUpCfg
xldv20AdcMarginUpCfg.description: Desired upstream margin. The unit of measurement is dB.

xldv20AdcMinMarginDnCfg.name: xldv20AdcMinMarginDnCfg
xldv20AdcMinMarginDnCfg.description: Desired threshold for downstream margin in units of dB. If the value auto is selected during configuration the threshold is calculated from the configured margin : threshold margin down = configured margin down - 6 dB.

xldv20AdcMinMarginUpCfg.name: xldv20AdcMinMarginUpCfg
xldv20AdcMinMarginUpCfg.description: Desired threshold for upstream margin in units of dB. If the value auto is selected during configuration the threshold is calculated from the configured margin : threshold margin up = configured margin up - 6 dB.

xldv20AdcLatencyDnCfg.name: xldv20AdcLatencyDnCfg
xldv20AdcLatencyDnCfg.description: The configured fast mode or interleaved mode downstream. 0 = interleavedLow (default). 1 = interleavedHigh . 256 = fast mode.

xldv20AdcLatencyUpCfg.name: xldv20AdcLatencyUpCfg
xldv20AdcLatencyUpCfg.description: The configured fast mode or interleaved mode upstream. 0 = interleavedLow (default). 1 = interleavedHigh . 256 = fast mode.

xldv20AdcRateDn.name: xldv20AdcRateDn
xldv20AdcRateDn.description: The current downstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 and 8096 Kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 19094 cells/sec. Default is rateInvalid (32767).

xldv20AdcRateUp.name: xldv20AdcRateUp
xldv20AdcRateUp.description: The current upstream data rate. The data rate ranges from 32 and 768 kbit/sec and is splitted into units of 32 Kbit/sec. This corresponds to a cell rate between 75 and 1811 cells/sec. Default is rateInvalid (32767).

xldv20AdcMarginDn.name: xldv20AdcMarginDn
xldv20AdcMarginDn.description: The current downstream margin in units of dB. Default is marginInvalid.

xldv20AdcMarginUp.name: xldv20AdcMarginUp
xldv20AdcMarginUp.description: The current upstream margin in units of dB. Default is marginInvalid.

xldv20AdcAttenuationDn.name: xldv20AdcAttenuationDn
xldv20AdcAttenuationDn.description: The current downstream attenuation in steps of 0,5 dB. Default is attenuationInvalid .

xldv20AdcAttenuationUp.name: xldv20AdcAttenuationUp
xldv20AdcAttenuationUp.description: The current upstream attenuation in steps of 0,5 dB. Default is attenuationInvalid .

xldv20AdcLinkState.name: xldv20AdcLinkState
xldv20AdcLinkState.description: The attribute reflects upon the internal states of the Central Office Modem.

xldv20AdcAISOnLOS.name: xldv20AdcAISOnLOS
xldv20AdcAISOnLOS.description: Enables or disables the VP-AIS generation after defect LOS.

xldv20AdcAISOnACT.name: xldv20AdcAISOnACT
xldv20AdcAISOnACT.description: Enables or disables the VP-AIS generation after link activation fault.

xldv20AdcXdslServiceTypeCfg.name: xldv20AdcXdslServiceTypeCfg
xldv20AdcXdslServiceTypeCfg.description: The configured service mode for XDSL line.

xldv20AdcInitStatus.name: xldv20AdcInitStatus
xldv20AdcInitStatus.description: The initialization status field of an ADSL line. Describes the initalization error in case of an activation problem on an ADSL line .

xldv20AdcTransceiverOutputPower.name: xldv20AdcTransceiverOutputPower
xldv20AdcTransceiverOutputPower.description: The ADSL tranceiver output power. Granularity 1.0 dBm. Default value is outputPowerInvalid.

xldv20AdcFirstUsedSubCarrierUpstream.name: xldv20AdcFirstUsedSubCarrierUpstream
xldv20AdcFirstUsedSubCarrierUpstream.description: The first used sub carrier in upstream direction. Default value is 64 (unknown).

xldv20AdcFirstUsedSubCarrierDownstream.name: xldv20AdcFirstUsedSubCarrierDownstream
xldv20AdcFirstUsedSubCarrierDownstream.description: The first used sub carrier in downstream direction. Default value is 256 (unknown).

xldv20AdcLastUsedSubCarrierUpstream.name: xldv20AdcLastUsedSubCarrierUpstream
xldv20AdcLastUsedSubCarrierUpstream.description: The last used sub carrier in upstream direction. Default value is 64 (unknown).

xldv20AdcLastUsedSubCarrierDownstream.name: xldv20AdcLastUsedSubCarrierDownstream
xldv20AdcLastUsedSubCarrierDownstream.description: The last used sub carrier in downstream direction. Default value is 256 (unknown).

xldv20AdcXdslServiceType.name: xldv20AdcXdslServiceType
xldv20AdcXdslServiceType.description: The current service type resulting from the configured service type. It depends on the actual hardware. Configuring gDotHsMode can result either in gDotLiteMode or gDotDmtMode. gDotAll can result in gDotDmtMode, ansiT1dot413 or gDotLiteMode. Default value is serviceTypeUnknown (10).

xldv20VdcPPTPTable.name: xldv20VdcPPTPTable
xldv20VdcPPTPTable.description: Feature not supported. The physical path termination point table for VDSL C.

xldv20VdcPPTPEntry.name: xldv20VdcPPTPEntry
xldv20VdcPPTPEntry.description: An entry describing a termination point in the PPTP table. Notifications : see xldv20IfEntry.

xldv20VdcMinRateDnCfg.description: The lower limit of the downstream data rate.

xldv20VdcMinRateUpCfg.name: xldv20VdcMinRateUpCfg
xldv20VdcMinRateUpCfg.description: The lower limit of the upstream data rate.

xldv20VdcMaxRateDnCfg.description: The upper limit of the downstream data rate.

xldv20VdcMaxRateUpCfg.name: xldv20VdcMaxRateUpCfg
xldv20VdcMaxRateUpCfg.description: The upper limit of the upstream data rate.

xldv20VdcLatencyDnCfg.description: Desired interleave depth (i.e. latency time) used for error correction in downstream direction.

xldv20VdcLatencyUpCfg.name: xldv20VdcLatencyUpCfg
xldv20VdcLatencyUpCfg.description: Desired interleave depth (i.e. latency time) used for error correction in upstream direction.

xldv20VdcPsdMaskCfg.description: Desired PSD mask option (electro-magnetic interference effects, M1 for strong and M2 for weak effects).

xldv20VdcMarginDn.name: xldv20VdcMarginDn
xldv20VdcMarginDn.description: The current downstream margin in units of dB.

xldv20VdcMarginUp.description: The current upstream margin in units of dB.

xldv20VdcAttenuationDn.name: xldv20VdcAttenuationDn
xldv20VdcAttenuationDn.description: The current downstream attenuation in units of dB.

xldv20VdcAttenuationUp.name: xldv20VdcAttenuationUp
xldv20VdcAttenuationUp.description: The current upstream attenuation in units of dB.

xldv20VdcLinkState.name: xldv20VdcLinkState
xldv20VdcLinkState.description: Current internal states of the Central Office VDSL Modem.

xldv20IbmPPTPTable.name: xldv20IbmPPTPTable
xldv20IbmPPTPTable.description: The physical path termination point table for the IBM IF.

xldv20IbmPPTPEntry.name: xldv20IbmPPTPEntry
xldv20IbmPPTPEntry.description: An entry describing a termination point in the IbmPPTP table. Notifications : see xldv20IfEntry.

xldv20IbmAISOnLOS.name: xldv20IbmAISOnLOS
xldv20IbmAISOnLOS.description: To enable/disable (default) the VP-AIS generation on defect LOS.

xldv20IbmVpAISFiltering.name: xldv20IbmVpAISFiltering
xldv20IbmVpAISFiltering.description: To enable or disable (default) the VP-AIS cell filtering function in the NT. In case of enable no VP-AIS cells are passed to the subscriber.

xldv20Ds3NePPTPTable.name: xldv20Ds3NePPTPTable
xldv20Ds3NePPTPTable.description: The near end physical path termination point table for the DS3 interface.

xldv20Ds3NePPTPEntry.name: xldv20Ds3NePPTPEntry
xldv20Ds3NePPTPEntry.description: An entry describing a termination point in the PPTP table. Notifications : see xldv20IfEntry.

xldv20D3nType.name: xldv20D3nType
xldv20D3nType.description: The interface type of the line used for transmission.

xldv20D3nCodingType.name: xldv20D3nCodingType
xldv20D3nCodingType.description: The coding type of the line used for transmission. Value: dsx3B3ZS .

xldv20E3NePPTPTable.name: xldv20E3NePPTPTable
xldv20E3NePPTPTable.description: The physical path termination point table for the E3 IF.

xldv20E3NePPTPEntry.name: xldv20E3NePPTPEntry
xldv20E3NePPTPEntry.description: An entry describing a termination point in the PPTP table. Notifications : see xldv20IfEntry.

xldv20E3nType.name: xldv20E3nType
xldv20E3nType.description: The interface type of the line used for transmission.

xldv20E3nCodingType.name: xldv20E3nCodingType
xldv20E3nCodingType.description: The coding type of the line used for transmission.

xldv20E3nTrailTraceSend.name: xldv20E3nTrailTraceSend
xldv20E3nTrailTraceSend.description: The pattern to be sent to LE for the trail trace send functionality.

xldv20E3nTrailTraceSendDefault.name: xldv20E3nTrailTraceSendDefault
xldv20E3nTrailTraceSendDefault.description: To configure the trail trace send functionality. A default trace value (enabled) or the pattern defined in the xldv20E3nTrailTraceSend attribute (disabled) will be sent.

xldv20E3nTrailTraceExpect.name: xldv20E3nTrailTraceExpect
xldv20E3nTrailTraceExpect.description: The expected pattern. It will be compared with the value of the E3nTrailTraceReceive attribute provided that the attribute E3nTrailTraceTIMDetection is enabled.

xldv20E3nTrailTraceTIMDetectionActivate.name: xldv20E3nTrailTraceTIMDetectionActivate

xldv20Dsx1LineType.name: xldv20Dsx1LineType
xldv20Dsx1LineType.description: This variable indicates the variety of DS1 Line implementing this circuit. The type of circuit affects the number of bits per second that the circuit can reasonably carry, as well as the interpretation of the usage and error statistics. The values, in sequence. dsx1ESF Extended SuperFrame DS1. dsx1D4 AT&T D4 format DS1. dsx1E1 CCITT Recommendation G704 (Table 4a). dsx1E1-CRC CCITT Recommendation G704 (Table 4b). dsxE1-MF G704 (Table 4a) with TS16 multiframing enabled. dsx1E1-CRC-MF G704 (Table 4b) with TS16. multiframing enabled.

xldv20Dsx1LineCoding.name: xldv20Dsx1LineCoding
xldv20Dsx1LineCoding.description: This variable describes the variety of Zero Code Suppression used on the link, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. dsx1JBZS refers the Jammed Bit Zero Suppres- sion, in which the AT&T specification of at least one pulse every 8 bit periods is literal- ly implemented by forcing a pulse in bit 8 of each channel. Thus, only seven bits per chan- nel, or 1.344 Mbps, is available for data. dsx1B8ZS refers to the use of a specified pat- tern of normal bits and bipolar violations which are used to replace a sequence of eight zero bits. ANSI Clear Channels may use dsx1ZBTSI, or Zero Byte Time Slot Interchange. E1 links, with or without CRC, use dsx1HDB3 or dsx1AMI. dsx1AMI refers to a mode wherein no zero code suppression is present and the line encoding does not solve the problem directly. In this application, the higher layer must provide data which meets or exceeds the pulse density re- quirements, such as inverting HDLC data.

xldv20Dsx1LoopbackConfig.name: xldv20Dsx1LoopbackConfig
xldv20Dsx1LoopbackConfig.description: This variable represents the loopback confi- guration of the DS1 interface. Agents support- ing read/write access should return badValue in response to a requested loopback state that the interface does not support. The values mean:. dsx1NoLoop Not in the loopback state. A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as it's value. dsx1PayloadLoop The received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for re- transmission after it has passed through the device's framing function. dsx1LineLoop The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum pene- tration) but is looped back out. dsx1OtherLoop Loopbacks that are not defined here.

xldv20Dsx1SignalMode.name: xldv20Dsx1SignalMode
xldv20Dsx1SignalMode.description: The signal mode. 'none' indicates that no bits are reserved for signaling on this channel. 'robbedBit' indicates that T1 Robbed Bit Sig- naling is in use. 'bitOriented' indicates that E1 Channel Asso- ciated Signaling is in use. 'messageOriented' indicates that Common Chan- nel Signaling is in use either on channel 16 of an E1 link or channel 24 of a T1.

xldv20Dsx1TransmitClockSource.name: xldv20Dsx1TransmitClockSource
xldv20Dsx1TransmitClockSource.description: The source of Transmit Clock. 'loopTiming' indicates that the recovered re- ceive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'localTiming' indicates that a local clock source is used. 'throughTiming' indicates that recovered re- ceive clock from another interface is used as the transmit clock.

xldv20Dsx1Fdl.name: xldv20Dsx1Fdl
xldv20Dsx1Fdl.description: This bitmap describes the use of the facili- ties data link, and is the sum of the capabili- ties: 'other' indicates that a protocol other than one following is used. 'dsx1Ansi-T1-403' refers to the FDL exchange recommended by ANSI. 'dsx1Att-54016' refers to ESF FDL exchanges. 'dsx1Fdl-none' indicates that the device does not use the FDL.
