xldv20ImaLinkOifAnomalies.description: The number of OIF anomalies, except during SES-IMA or UAS-IMA conditions, at the near-end. This is an optional attribute.

xldv20ImaLinkNeSevErroredSecs.name: xldv20ImaLinkNeSevErroredSecs
xldv20ImaLinkNeSevErroredSecs.description: Count of one second intervals containing >= 30% of the ICP cells counted as IV-IMAs, or one or more link defects (e.g., LOS, OOF/LOF, AIS, or LCD), LIF defects, or LODS defects, except during UAS-IMA condition.

xldv20ImaLinkFeSevErroredSecs.name: xldv20ImaLinkFeSevErroredSecs
xldv20ImaLinkFeSevErroredSecs.description: Count of one second intervals containing one or more RDI-IMA defects, except during UAS-IMA-FE condition.

xldv20ImaLinkNeUnavailSecs.name: xldv20ImaLinkNeUnavailSecs
xldv20ImaLinkNeUnavailSecs.description: Count of unavailable seconds at near-end: unavailability begins at the onset of 10 contiguous SES-IMA and ends at the onset of 10 contiguous seconds with no SES-IMA.

xldv20ImaLinkFeUnavailSecs.name: xldv20ImaLinkFeUnavailSecs
xldv20ImaLinkFeUnavailSecs.description: Count of unavailable seconds at near-end: unavailability begins at the onset of 10 contiguous SES-IMA-FE and ends at the onset of 10 contiguous seconds with no SES-IMA-FE.

xldv20ImaLinkNeTxUnusableSecs.name: xldv20ImaLinkNeTxUnusableSecs
xldv20ImaLinkNeTxUnusableSecs.description: Tx Unusable seconds: count of Tx Unusable seconds at the near-end Tx LSM.

xldv20ImaLinkNeRxUnusableSecs.name: xldv20ImaLinkNeRxUnusableSecs
xldv20ImaLinkNeRxUnusableSecs.description: Rx Unusable seconds: count of Rx Unusable seconds at the near-end Rx LSM.

xldv20ImaLinkFeTxUnusableSecs.name: xldv20ImaLinkFeTxUnusableSecs
xldv20ImaLinkFeTxUnusableSecs.description: Tx Unusable seconds: count of Tx Unusable seconds at the far-end Tx LSM.

xldv20ImaLinkFeRxUnusableSecs.name: xldv20ImaLinkFeRxUnusableSecs
xldv20ImaLinkFeRxUnusableSecs.description: Rx Unusable seconds: count of Rx Unusable seconds at the far-end Rx LSM.

xldv20ImaLinkNeTxNumFailures.name: xldv20ImaLinkNeTxNumFailures
xldv20ImaLinkNeTxNumFailures.description: The number of times a near-end transmit failure alarm condition has been entered on this link (i.e., some form of implementation specific transmit fault).

xldv20ImaLinkNeRxNumFailures.name: xldv20ImaLinkNeRxNumFailures
xldv20ImaLinkNeRxNumFailures.description: The number of times a near-end receive failure alarm condition has been entered on this link (i.e., LIF, LODS, RFI-IMA, Mis-Connected or some form of implementation specific receive fault).

xldv20ImaLinkFeTxNumFailures.name: xldv20ImaLinkFeTxNumFailures
xldv20ImaLinkFeTxNumFailures.description: The number of times a far-end transmit failure alarm condition has been entered on this link (i.e., Tx-Unusable-FE). This is an optional attribute.

xldv20ImaLinkFeRxNumFailures.name: xldv20ImaLinkFeRxNumFailures
xldv20ImaLinkFeRxNumFailures.description: The number of times a far-end receive failure alarm condition has been entered on this link (i.e., Rx-Unusable-FE). This is an optional attribute.

xldv20ImaLinkTxStuffs.name: xldv20ImaLinkTxStuffs
xldv20ImaLinkTxStuffs.description: Count of stuff events inserted in the transmit direction. This is an optional attribute.

xldv20ImaLinkRxStuffs.name: xldv20ImaLinkRxStuffs
xldv20ImaLinkRxStuffs.description: Count of stuff events inserted in the receive direction. This is an optional attribute.

xldv20LbpEntry.name: xldv20LbpEntry
xldv20LbpEntry.description: An entry in the loop back point table. The entry holds parameters of loop back points (as the loop location ID for loop back points or the loop mode). Loopback points are either the TCA at the LU* or SU or the IMA group at the LUIMA (within the DSLAM), or the TCA of adrPPTP at the NTAD. Notifications : see xldv20IfEntry.

xldv20LbpLoopLocId.name: xldv20LbpLoopLocId
xldv20LbpLoopLocId.description: A unique number known by the crafts person specifying the location where the OAM loopback cell shall be looped back. Loopback point is either the TCA at the LU* or SU (within the DSLAM) or the TCA of adrPPTP at NTAD. NOTE : Due to the functionality of ASPEN at SU the loop location ID only of port 1 is configurable. The IDs for port2-16 are calculated from this value by the ASPEN. TMN will store these values to the corresponding table entries .

xldv20LbpLoopMode.name: xldv20LbpLoopMode
xldv20LbpLoopMode.description: This attribute selects for connecting points whether the received loopback cell shall be forwarded or forwarded and looped back .

xldv20PltIfIndex.name: xldv20PltIfIndex
xldv20PltIfIndex.description: This attribute labels the location of the physical loopback. It can be the ifIndex of a PPTP at LI25, LU, SU .

xldv20PltControlReq.name: xldv20PltControlReq
xldv20PltControlReq.description: The received command to start an OAM cell loopback test (loopDiagRequest). Notifications : xldv20TrPltTestResult .

xldv20PltControlStatus.name: xldv20PltControlStatus
xldv20PltControlStatus.description: The status of the control request.

xldv20PltControlTimer.name: xldv20PltControlTimer
xldv20PltControlTimer.description: This is the maximum duration of a physical loop diagnosis. It is required by the SNMP manager to detect the end of a physical loop diagnosis in case of the response 'xldv20TrPltTestResult' was not received in time.

xldv20PltControlReqResult.name: xldv20PltControlReqResult
xldv20PltControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20PltControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20PltControlTimeStamp
xldv20PltControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20AltIfIndex.name: xldv20AltIfIndex
xldv20AltIfIndex.description: The TLM interface where OAM cells are inserted. It can be the 'IfIndex' of a PPTP at a LU or SU.

xldv20AltVpi.name: xldv20AltVpi
xldv20AltVpi.description: Identifies the VPI which shall be tested. It is VPINni when test in LE direction or it is VPIUni when test in NT direction.

xldv20AltLoopLocId.name: xldv20AltLoopLocId
xldv20AltLoopLocId.description: Test cell loopback location. It is an identifier known by the crafts person identifying a ATM node in the ATM network. For EndToEnd loop test the default value is valid.

xldv20AltControlReq.name: xldv20AltControlReq
xldv20AltControlReq.description: The received command to start an OAM cell loopback test (loopTestRequest). Reject reasons are faulty parameters from the agent (response: paramFaulty, commExecStarted, loopTestReject, commandFailed) or a loop request during a running test (response: loopTestBusy). Notifications : xldv20TrAltTestResult .

xldv20AltControlStatus.name: xldv20AltControlStatus
xldv20AltControlStatus.description: The status of the command handling.

xldv20AltControlTimer.name: xldv20AltControlTimer
xldv20AltControlTimer.description: The maximum duration of loop- back test. It is required by the SNMP manager to detect the end of loopback test in case of the response'xldv20TrAltTestResult' was not received in time.

xldv20AltOamLevel.name: xldv20AltOamLevel
xldv20AltOamLevel.description: The OAM level for loop test on VP/VC level. Valid: f4 (for VP ) f5 (for VC).

xldv20AltLoopTestType.name: xldv20AltLoopTestType
xldv20AltLoopTestType.description: The type of loop test . For EndToEnd loop test loop location ID is FF..FF.

xldv20AltVci.name: xldv20AltVci
xldv20AltVci.description: Insertion point for OAM cells for F5 level

xldv20AltControlReqResult.name: xldv20AltControlReqResult
xldv20AltControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20AltFlowDirection.name: xldv20AltFlowDirection
xldv20AltFlowDirection.description: Labels the flow direction of loop back cells. 'inwards' meanxing towards cellbus. 'outwards' meaning towards UTOPIA interface .

xldv20AltControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20AltControlTimeStamp
xldv20AltControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20MultipleLoopbackResultTable.name: xldv20MultipleLoopbackResultTable
xldv20MultipleLoopbackResultTable.description: The Multiple Loopback Result table. Used for the multiple loopback functionality to collect the IDs of connecting points which looped back to the XLD. When an ATM looptest is started the table is empty. An entry is created when an OAM cell is received from a connecting point.

xldv20MlbEntry.name: xldv20MlbEntry
xldv20MlbEntry.description: An entry in the Multiple Loopback Result Table.

xldv20MlbLoopLocId.name: xldv20MlbLoopLocId
xldv20MlbLoopLocId.description: A unique number known by the crafts person specifying the ID of a connecting point which looped back an OAM cell to the originating point (SU or LU) within the XLD.

xldv20ExternalAlarmsTable.name: xldv20ExternalAlarmsTable
xldv20ExternalAlarmsTable.description: The entities of the table are used to control the forwarding of external alarms to the TMN-OS and LCT.

xldv20ExternalAlarmEntry.name: xldv20ExternalAlarmEntry
xldv20ExternalAlarmEntry.description: Entry of external alarm table. Notifications : xldv20TrExternalAlarm.

xldv20ExtAlarmIndex.name: xldv20ExtAlarmIndex
xldv20ExtAlarmIndex.description: A unique number identifying an entry of the external alarm table.

xldv20ExtAlarmAdminState.name: xldv20ExtAlarmAdminState
xldv20ExtAlarmAdminState.description: This attribute is used to activate (unlock) and deactivate (lock) the forwarding of the external alarm towards the manager.

xldv20ExtAlarmOperState.name: xldv20ExtAlarmOperState
xldv20ExtAlarmOperState.description: Indicates whether or not the external alarm is capable of performing its normal functions.

xldv20ExtAlarmActivityState.name: xldv20ExtAlarmActivityState
xldv20ExtAlarmActivityState.description: The status of the external alarm. Only if the operational state is enabled and the alarm state is on, an external alarm is generated for this object.

xldv20ExtAlarmSeverityIndex.name: xldv20ExtAlarmSeverityIndex
xldv20ExtAlarmSeverityIndex.description: The index of the associated entry in the alarm severity profile table. These entries contain the severity assigments for the alarms reported by this managed entity.

xldv20ExtAlarmFilteringIndex.name: xldv20ExtAlarmFilteringIndex
xldv20ExtAlarmFilteringIndex.description: It is a pointer to the instance of the alarm filtering assignment profile managed entity that contains the filtering assignments for the alarms reported by this managed entity.

xldv20ExtAlarmName.name: xldv20ExtAlarmName
xldv20ExtAlarmName.description: Describe the input line and the type of external alarm. Default values on startup are : index=1 : Fan 1 Fail index=2 : Fan 2 Fail index=3 : High Temperature.

xldv20AlarmSeverityProfileTable.name: xldv20AlarmSeverityProfileTable
xldv20AlarmSeverityProfileTable.description: The table of alarm severity profiles. Profiles can be created or deleted dynamically. Creating or deleting an entry in this table automatically creates or deletes the corresponding entries in the xldv20AlarmSevTable.

xldv20AlarmSeverityProfileEntry.name: xldv20AlarmSeverityProfileEntry
xldv20AlarmSeverityProfileEntry.description: A group of severities, one for each alarm type in the communications alarm group.

xldv20AlmSevProfileIndex.name: xldv20AlmSevProfileIndex
xldv20AlmSevProfileIndex.description: A number identifying this alarm severity profile.

xldv20AlmSevProfileRowStatus.name: xldv20AlmSevProfileRowStatus
xldv20AlmSevProfileRowStatus.description: Used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table. Default value: xldv20AlmSevProfileIndex = 1..10: created xldv20AlmSevProfileIndex = 11..40: deleted .

xldv20AlarmSeverityTable.name: xldv20AlarmSeverityTable
xldv20AlarmSeverityTable.description: The alarm severity table associates profile index and trap ID pairs with severities to be used for alarm traps that have occurred. (Note that this table does not apply to cleared alarms).

xldv20AlarmSeverityEntry.name: xldv20AlarmSeverityEntry
xldv20AlarmSeverityEntry.description: An entry in this table associates an alarm severity profile index/trap ID pair with a severity to be used for alarm traps. The alarm severity profile index is referenced by the 'Alarm Severity assignment Profile Pointer' attribute in the alarm-reporting managed entity e.g. plug-in unit and TLM interface (tcAdaptor, Physical Path Termination Point etc.). Notifications : none.

xldv20AlmSevTrapId.name: xldv20AlmSevTrapId
xldv20AlmSevTrapId.description: The trap ID of the alarm trap type this entry applies to. NOTE : the severity of xldv20TrAtmLayerMultiAlarm is not configurable.

xldv20AlmSeverity.name: xldv20AlmSeverity
xldv20AlmSeverity.description: The severity to be used for this trap type when the entry is selected.

xldv20AlarmFilteringProfileTable.name: xldv20AlarmFilteringProfileTable
xldv20AlarmFilteringProfileTable.description: The table of alarm filtering profiles. Creating or deleting an entry in this table automatically creates or deletes the corresponding entries in the xldv20AlarmFilteringTable.

xldv20AlarmFilteringProfileEntry.name: xldv20AlarmFilteringProfileEntry
xldv20AlarmFilteringProfileEntry.description: An entry of the alarm filtering profile table.

xldv20AlmFiltProfileIndex.name: xldv20AlmFiltProfileIndex
xldv20AlmFiltProfileIndex.description: A number identifying this alarm filtering profile.

xldv20AlmFiltProfileRowStatus.name: xldv20AlmFiltProfileRowStatus
xldv20AlmFiltProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table. Default value: xldv20AlmFiltProfileIndex = 1: created xldv20AlmFiltProfileIndex = 2 .. 300: deleted .

xldv20AlarmFilteringTable.name: xldv20AlarmFilteringTable
xldv20AlarmFilteringTable.description: The alarm filtering table is used for temporairy filtering of alarms.

xldv20AlarmFilteringEntry.name: xldv20AlarmFilteringEntry
xldv20AlarmFilteringEntry.description: An entry in this table associates a trap id/ temporal filter parameter with a xldv20AlmFiltProfileIndex.

xldv20AlmFiltTrapId.name: xldv20AlmFiltTrapId
xldv20AlmFiltTrapId.description: The ID of the trap type this entry applies to.

xldv20AlmTempFilter.name: xldv20AlmTempFilter
xldv20AlmTempFilter.description: The temporal filtering period in seconds. The value 0 means no filtering.

xldv20AlarmListTable.name: xldv20AlarmListTable
xldv20AlarmListTable.description: The alarm list table is used to store all reported alarms.

xldv20AlarmListEntry.name: xldv20AlarmListEntry
xldv20AlarmListEntry.description: Entry of the alarm list table. Notifications : none.

xldv20AlmIndex.name: xldv20AlmIndex
xldv20AlmIndex.description: Unique value to identify an entry in the alarm list when the entry is read or cleared, when the entry is created.

xldv20AlmNatureOfAlarm.name: xldv20AlmNatureOfAlarm
xldv20AlmNatureOfAlarm.description: Generic trouble description of an alarm (the trap ID).

xldv20AlmSpecProblem.name: xldv20AlmSpecProblem
xldv20AlmSpecProblem.description: Description of further information about an alarm.

xldv20AlmSpecProblemText.name: xldv20AlmSpecProblemText
xldv20AlmSpecProblemText.description: Description of further information about an alarm in text form.

xldv20AlmRepEntityId.name: xldv20AlmRepEntityId
xldv20AlmRepEntityId.description: The managed entity that reported the alarm. In case of a HWM / TLM / COH / GFH object it is the HW unit index / interface index / vpcTP or vccTp index / External Alarm index.

xldv20AlmFailedComponent.name: xldv20AlmFailedComponent
xldv20AlmFailedComponent.description: The managed entity which is defective.

xldv20AlmFailedComponentRepSource.name: xldv20AlmFailedComponentRepSource
xldv20AlmFailedComponentRepSource.description: The SW application isolating the failed component.

xldv20AlmPropRepairAction.name: xldv20AlmPropRepairAction
xldv20AlmPropRepairAction.description: Suggestion of solutions to fix the problem.

xldv20AlmTimeAndDate.name: xldv20AlmTimeAndDate
xldv20AlmTimeAndDate.description: Entry time of the report into the log.

xldv20AlmControlReq.name: xldv20AlmControlReq
xldv20AlmControlReq.description: Marks the received command to update the alarm list (updateAlmList) or the alarming filtering table (updateFiltList) or the request of Atm layer multi alarm traps (startSendingAlarms).

xldv20AlmControlStatus.name: xldv20AlmControlStatus
xldv20AlmControlStatus.description: The status of the control request. The value requestIdle will be set after startup/recovery or after a running test was aborted by the SNMP manager.

xldv20AlmControlReqResult.name: xldv20AlmControlReqResult
xldv20AlmControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20AlmControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20AlmControlTimeStamp
xldv20AlmControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20RstControlReq.name: xldv20RstControlReq
xldv20RstControlReq.description: Request to perform a reset. Notifications : xldv20TrReplaceableUnitReset at beginning of reset PIU. xldv20TrReplaceableUnitResetEnd at end of reset PIU. xldv20TrRstResult for reset of CI in case of a failure occured after the reset has been accepted.

xldv20RstControlStatus.name: xldv20RstControlStatus
xldv20RstControlStatus.description: The actual status of the reset procedure.

xldv20RstLevel.name: xldv20RstLevel
xldv20RstLevel.description: The reset level. With this attribute the TMN-OS can deside to make a reset for one unit or the whole system.

xldv20RstHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20RstHwUnitIndex
xldv20RstHwUnitIndex.description: The (HwUnitIndex) of the plugin unit which should get the reset.

xldv20RstControlTimer.name: xldv20RstControlTimer
xldv20RstControlTimer.description: Timer value for the trap response. Only valid if xldv20RstControlStatus indicates requestBusy.

xldv20RstControlReqResult.name: xldv20RstControlReqResult
xldv20RstControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20RstControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20RstControlTimeStamp
xldv20RstControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20DbuControlReq.name: xldv20DbuControlReq
xldv20DbuControlReq.description: This attribute serves to launch a read request on either the Software Errorlog, the Software Tracelog or the Hardware Maintenancelog on the CI . From XLDV2.0 error logs and trace logs of PIUs of type SU,IL and LU are provided. Notifications : xldv20TrSweLogRead. xldv20TrHwmLogRead. xldv20TrTraceLogRead .

xldv20DbuControlStatus.name: xldv20DbuControlStatus
xldv20DbuControlStatus.description: The status of the current read request.

xldv20DbuResultFilePath.name: xldv20DbuResultFilePath
xldv20DbuResultFilePath.description: The path (including the file name) where the file resulting from the read request should be stored. If this attribute does not contain a valid path the results will be printed on screen.

xldv20DbuLogType.name: xldv20DbuLogType
xldv20DbuLogType.description: The log to be read by the read request.

xldv20DbuNumEntries.name: xldv20DbuNumEntries
xldv20DbuNumEntries.description: The number of log entries to be read. If it is 0 or if the passed number exceeds the number of entries mandatoryly in the log, the entire log will be read.

xldv20DbuControlTimer.name: xldv20DbuControlTimer
xldv20DbuControlTimer.description: The timer value for trap response.

xldv20DbuControlReqResult.name: xldv20DbuControlReqResult
xldv20DbuControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20DbuHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20DbuHwUnitIndex
xldv20DbuHwUnitIndex.description: The HwUnitIndex of the plug-in unit which log should be read.

xldv20DbuControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20DbuControlTimeStamp
xldv20DbuControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20SucUnit.name: xldv20SucUnit
xldv20SucUnit.description: The plug-in unit type to be upgraded.

xldv20SucAllOfType.name: xldv20SucAllOfType
xldv20SucAllOfType.description: Indicates that the loading for the dedicated unit type may be started n-times ( sucUpgrAll ) regarding to the number of boards of the same type within the DSLAM or for a single unit (sucUpgrSingle ).

xldv20SucVersionNo.name: xldv20SucVersionNo
xldv20SucVersionNo.description: String containing the APS version coded into the load for the different board types (destination version). Default value is \0. Then the default SW version should be loaded.

xldv20SucHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20SucHwUnitIndex
xldv20SucHwUnitIndex.description: The hardware unit index of the plug-in unit to be loaded in case of an single upgrade.

xldv20SucPathName.name: xldv20SucPathName
xldv20SucPathName.description: The pathname of SAPS content file.

xldv20SucFileName.name: xldv20SucFileName
xldv20SucFileName.description: The filename of SAPS content file.

xldv20SucControlReq.name: xldv20SucControlReq
xldv20SucControlReq.description: SW upgrade command requests from TMN. Notifications : xldv20TrCmuReadyForReset. xldv20TrUnitReadyForReset. xldv20TrActivateLoadResult. xldv20TrPuUpgradeResult. xldv20TrFTPError. xldv20TrUpgradeCanceled. xldv20TrSwVersionsSet. xldv20TrReadSAPSContentFileReady. xldv20TrUpgradeEndRequestResult. xldv20TrUnitUpgradeNotRequested.

xldv20SucControlStatus.name: xldv20SucControlStatus
xldv20SucControlStatus.description: The status of the current request.

xldv20SucControlTimer.name: xldv20SucControlTimer
xldv20SucControlTimer.description: Wait time in seconds after complete upgrade for a unit type.

xldv20SucNumberOfTraps.name: xldv20SucNumberOfTraps
xldv20SucNumberOfTraps.description: Number of traps which have to be expected.

xldv20SucDefaultSwVersion.name: xldv20SucDefaultSwVersion
xldv20SucDefaultSwVersion.description: The default SW version. Result of the command GetSwVersions.

xldv20SucPredecessorSwVersion.name: xldv20SucPredecessorSwVersion
xldv20SucPredecessorSwVersion.description: The predecessor Sw version. Result of the command GetSwVersions.

xldv20SucPrePredecessorSwVersion.name: xldv20SucPrePredecessorSwVersion
xldv20SucPrePredecessorSwVersion.description: The pre predecessor Sw version. Result of the command GetSwVersions.

xldv20SucControlReqResult.name: xldv20SucControlReqResult
xldv20SucControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

xldv20SucControlTimeStamp.name: xldv20SucControlTimeStamp
xldv20SucControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

xldv20SwUpgradeTaskTable.name: xldv20SwUpgradeTaskTable
xldv20SwUpgradeTaskTable.description: Table of the current active or failed tasks of SW upgrade. Entries for successfull loading tasks are removed from the table. This table is used to display the upgrade status for single plugin units at the TMN.

xldv20SutTaskTableEntry.name: xldv20SutTaskTableEntry
xldv20SutTaskTableEntry.description: Entry of the SW upgrade task table. Notifications : none.

xldv20SutIndex.name: xldv20SutIndex
xldv20SutIndex.description: Unique value to identify an entry of this table.

xldv20SutPiuType.name: xldv20SutPiuType
xldv20SutPiuType.description: Indicates the plug-in unit type to be upgraded.

xldv20SutHwUnitIndex.name: xldv20SutHwUnitIndex
xldv20SutHwUnitIndex.description: The HwUnitIndex of PIU to be loaded. From this value the TMN calculates the location shelf/slot of the plug-in unit and displays it at the GUI.

xldv20SutSwVersion.name: xldv20SutSwVersion
xldv20SutSwVersion.description: String containing the APS version which is loaded into the plug-in unit .

xldv20SutRequester.name: xldv20SutRequester
xldv20SutRequester.description: Identifies the requesting unit of the current upgrade task.

xldv20SutUpgradeState.name: xldv20SutUpgradeState
xldv20SutUpgradeState.description: Identifies the current processing state of the upgrade task.

xldv20SutUpgradeResult.name: xldv20SutUpgradeResult
xldv20SutUpgradeResult.description: This read-only attribute informs about the result of the performes upgrade (in case of failed upgrade the error reason).

xldv20SutTimeStamp.name: xldv20SutTimeStamp
xldv20SutTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the task. It is updated anytime the upgrade task state changes.

xldv20StcTelnetAccess.name: xldv20StcTelnetAccess
xldv20StcTelnetAccess.description: Feature not supported. The access mode of a telnet session. The setting of values read, trace, write will enable a secure telnet session with the corresponding access right. The setting of value noAccess will disable a telnet session.

xldv20DbmControlReq.name: xldv20DbmControlReq
xldv20DbmControlReq.description: The command to store the database (backupDb) into the FEPROM of the DSLAM. The return value commExecStarted indicates the beginning of DB storage. Notifications : xldv20TrDbBackup indicates the end and the result of the database storage.

xldv20DbmControlStatus.name: xldv20DbmControlStatus
xldv20DbmControlStatus.description: The status of the control request.

xldv20DbmControlTimer.name: xldv20DbmControlTimer
xldv20DbmControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager when a DB storage request cannot be executed immediately (value commExecStarted in the result attribute xldv20DbmControlReqResult). The manager reads this value from the DSLAM. The end of request indicates the trap xldv20TrDbBackup.

xldv20DbmBackupPeriod.name: xldv20DbmBackupPeriod
xldv20DbmBackupPeriod.description: Interval between two backup operations in hours.

xldv20DbmBackupStartTime.name: xldv20DbmBackupStartTime
xldv20DbmBackupStartTime.description: Start time of next DB backup in seconds.

xldv20DbmControlReqResultLocal.name: xldv20DbmControlReqResultLocal
xldv20DbmControlReqResultLocal.description: The result of the local backup request.

xldv20DbmControlReqResultRemote.name: xldv20DbmControlReqResultRemote
